<English>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’s marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’s Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.
<French>: La marque personnelle du chef d'escadron James Eric Storrar, de l'Escadron n° 65. La marque de Storrar est dérivée de l'insigne de l'Escadron n° 65, un lion passant - la position passante est celle où la patte avant droite du lion est levée, les autres étant posées sur le sol, un symbole héraldique commun qui représente la force, le courage et la générosité. Le marquage a été placé sous l'arrière de l'échappement du moteur du Spitfire Mk IX de Storrar, MH358.
<Italian>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’s marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’s Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.
<German>: "Löwe Passant" persönliches Motiv von Sqn Ldr J. E. Storrar, Nr. 65 Geschwader, RAF
<Spanish>: La marca personal del Líder de Escuadrón James Eric Storrar, Escuadrón No. 65. La marca de Storrar procede de la insignia del escuadrón No. 65, un león pasante — la posición de pasante es aquella en la que la pata delantera derecha del león está levantada con las otras en el suelo, un símbolo heráldico común que representa la fuerza, el valor y la generosidad. La marca se colocó bajo la parte trasera del escape del motor del Spitfire Mk IX de Storrar, MH358.
<Russian>: Эмблема "Лев", личный знак командира 65-й эскадрильи J. E. Storrar, RAF
<Polish>: Osobisty emblemat dowódcy dywizjonu Jamesa Erica Storrara, 65 Dywizjon. Emblemat Storrara pochodzi od odznaki dywizjonu 65, przedstawiającej lwa passant - w pozycji passant przednia prawa łapa lwa jest podniesiona, a pozostałe są na ziemi, co jest częstym symbolem heraldycznym oznaczającym siłę, odwagę i hojność. Emblemat był umieszczony pod tyłem wylotu silnika na Spitfire Mk IX, MH358 Storrara.
<Czech>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’s marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’s Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.
<Turkish>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’s marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’s Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 65 飞\t行\t中\t队\t指\t挥\t官\t詹\t姆\t斯·埃\t里\t克·斯\t托\t拉\t尔\t的\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦。\t标\t识\t飞\t行\t中\t队\t官\t方\t徽\t标\t中\t的\t雄\t狮\t纹\t章\t图\t案 - 纹\t章\t学\t中\t常\t见\t的\t狮\t子\t形\t象\t往\t往\t举\t起\t右\t前\t爪，\t其\t余\t脚\t爪\t立\t于\t地\t面\t上，\t被\t认\t为\t是\t力\t量、\t勇\t气\t与\t慷\t慨\t的\t象\t征。\t该\t涂\t鸦\t见\t于\t斯\t托\t拉\t尔\t编\t号 MH358 的\t喷\t火 Mk IX 战\t斗\t机\t引\t擎\t排\t气\t管\t后\t方\t的\t蒙\t皮\t位\t置。
<Japanese>: "Lion Passant" personal motif of Sqn Ldr J. E. Storrar, No. 65 Squadron, RAF
<Portuguese>: Motivo pessoal "Lion Passant" do Sqn Ldr J. E. Storrar, No. 65 Squadron, RAF
<Ukrainian>: Особисте маркування командира ескадрильї Джеймса Еріка Сторрара, 65-а ескадрилья. Маркування Сторрара походить від значка 65-ї ескадрильї, лев, що проходить — прохідна позиція — це місце, де передня права лапа лева піднята разом з іншими лапами на землі, що є загальним геральдичним символом сили, мужності та щедрості. Маркування було розміщено під задньою частиною вихлопу двигуна Spitfire Mk IX, MH358 Сторрара.
<Serbian>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’s marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’s Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.
<Hungarian>: J. E. Storrar századparancsnok személyes motívuma. Brit Királyi Légierő, 65. század.
<Korean>: 제65비행대장인 제임스 에릭 스토라의 개인 표식입니다. 스토라의 마킹에는 기존의 것과는 다르게 걷는 모습의 사자(lion passant) 이 그려져 있었는데, 사자의 오른쪽 앞발이 들린 채 다른 발은땅에 대고 있는 자세를 하고 있었습니다. 힘, 용기, 관대함을 상징한 이 마킹은 스토라의 스핏파이어 Mk IX, MH358의 엔진 배기구 뒤쪽 아래에 새겨져 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: "Lion Passant" personal motif of Sqn Ldr J. E. Storrar, No. 65 Squadron, RAF
<Romanian>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’s marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’s Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.
<TChinese>: Đánh dấu cá nhân của Đại tá James Eric Storrar, Sư đoàn số 65. Đánh dấu của Storrar được lấy từ huy hiệu của Sư đoàn số 65, một con sư tử passant - vị trí passant là khi chân trước bên phải của con sư tử được giơ lên với các chân khác trên mặt đất, một biểu tượng phong hào phổ biến đại diện cho sức mạnh, dũng cảm và lòng rộng lượng. Đánh dấu được đặt dưới phần sau của động cơ thoát khí trên chiếc Spitfire Mk IX, MH358 của Storrar.
<HChinese>: 英國皇家空軍第 65 中隊，中隊長 J·E·斯托拉“行進的雄獅”個人徽標
<Comments>: The personal marking of Squadron Leader James Eric Storrar, No. 65 Squadron. Storrar’\ts marking is derived from the Squadron badge of No. 65, a lion passant — the passant position is where the front right paw of the lion is raised with the others on the ground, a common heraldic symbol standing for strength, courage and generosity. The marking was placed under the back of the engine exhaust on Storrar’\ts Spitfire Mk IX, MH358.

<English>: The roundel of No. 34 Squadron, 1950s. Sometimes called a "Bar" or "Flash", these roundels were used to identify the aircraft of specific RAF squadrons, and consisted of a flashy pattern (usually derived from colors on the squadron’s badge) and either the standard RAF roundel or squadron emblem in the center. This pointed example was located on the side of the nose of Hawker Hunters in service with No. 34, with the tapered end pointing towards the front.
<French>: La cocarde de l'Escadron 34, dans les années 1950. Parfois appelées "Bar" ou "Flash", ces cocardes étaient utilisées pour identifier les avions d'escadrons spécifiques de la RAF et consistaient en un motif flash (généralement dérivé des couleurs de l'insigne de l'escadron) et, au centre, la cocarde standard de la RAF ou l'emblème de l'escadron. Cet exemple pointu se trouvait sur le côté du nez des Hawker Hunter en service au sein de la 34e escadrille, l'extrémité effilée pointant vers l'avant.
<Italian>: The roundel of No. 34 Squadron, 1950s. Sometimes called a "Bar" or "Flash", these roundels were used to identify the aircraft of specific RAF squadrons, and consisted of a flashy pattern (usually derived from colors on the squadron’s badge) and either the standard RAF roundel or squadron emblem in the center. This pointed example was located on the side of the nose of Hawker Hunters in service with No. 34, with the tapered end pointing towards the front.
<Spanish>: Escarapela del Escuadrón No. 34, años 50. A veces llamados "Bar" o "Flash", estas escarapelas se utilizaban para identificar los aviones de determinados escuadrones de la RAF, y consistían en un dibujo llamativo (normalmente derivado de los colores de la insignia del escuadrón) y la escarapela estándar de la RAF o el emblema del escuadrón en el centro. Este ejemplo puntiagudo estaba situado en el lateral del morro de los Hawker Hunter en servicio con el No. 34, con el extremo cónico apuntando hacia delante.
<Polish>: Kokarda 34 Dywizjonu, lata 50. Czasami nazywana "Bar" lub "Flash", kokardy te były używane do identyfikacji samolotów poszczególnych dywizjonów RAF i składały się z wyrazistego wzoru (zwykle wywodzącego się z kolorów na odznace dywizjonu) oraz standardowej kokardy RAF lub emblematu dywizjonu w centrum. Ten przykład, o zaostrzonym kształcie, znajdował się na boku nosa samolotów Hawker Hunter w służbie Dywizjonu 34, z wąskim końcem skierowanym do przodu.
<Czech>: The roundel of No. 34 Squadron, 1950s. Sometimes called a "Bar" or "Flash", these roundels were used to identify the aircraft of specific RAF squadrons, and consisted of a flashy pattern (usually derived from colors on the squadron’s badge) and either the standard RAF roundel or squadron emblem in the center. This pointed example was located on the side of the nose of Hawker Hunters in service with No. 34, with the tapered end pointing towards the front.
<Turkish>: The roundel of No. 34 Squadron, 1950s. This pointed example was located on the side of the nose of Hawker Hunters in service with No. 34, with the tapered end pointing towards the front.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 34 飞\t行\t中\t队\t在\t上\t世\t纪 50 年\t代\t期\t间\t使\t用\t的\t识\t别\t徽\t标。\t这\t一\t类\t标\t识\t主\t要\t用\t于\t辨\t识\t来\t自\t特\t定\t飞\t行\t中\t队\t的\t战\t机，\t一\t般\t称\t为\t“识\t别\t条\t带”\t或\t“部\t队\t略\t标”；\t识\t别\t条\t带\t的\t颜\t色\t直\t接\t取\t自\t部\t队\t徽\t标\t色\t块，\t中\t央\t饰\t以\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t标\t准\t圆\t徽\t或\t飞\t行\t中\t队\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t图\t样。\t该\t款\t识\t别\t徽\t标\t见\t于\t第 34 飞\t行\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t霍\t克\t“猎\t人”\t式\t战\t斗\t机\t座\t舱\t下\t方\t的\t蒙\t皮\t位\t置，\t箭\t头\t图\t案\t尖\t端\t指\t向\t机\t鼻\t前\t方。
<Ukrainian>: Рондель 34-ї ескадрильї, 1950-ті роки. Іноді їх називали «смугою» або «спалахом», ці круглі знаки використовувалися для ідентифікації літаків певних ескадрилій королівських ВПС і складалися з кричущого візерунка (зазвичай похідного від кольорів на значку ескадрильї) та/або стандартного круглого знака або емблеми ескадрильї в центрі. Цей загострений екземпляр був розташований збоку на носі Hawker Hunters на озброєнні у 34-ї, з конічним кінцем, спрямованим уперед.

<TChinese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Sư đoàn số 34, thập niên 1950. Đôi khi được gọi là một "Thanh" hoặc "Đèn", những huy hiệu tròn này được sử dụng để xác định các máy bay của các sư đoàn cụ thể của RAF, và bao gồm một mẫu huy hiệu nổi bật (thường được dựa trên các màu trên huy hiệu của sư đoàn) và ente hoặc huy hiệu của sư đoàn trong trung tâm. Ví dụ có hình nhọn này được đặt ở phía bên của mũi máy bay Hawker Hunters phục vụ với Sư đoàn số 34, với đầu nhọn hướng về phía trước.

<English>: Emblem of 4th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 26. The emblem depicts the head of a tiger, sporting a complicated expression. As the marking was quite intricate, the quality of the Tiger’s head differed substantially from aircraft to aircraft. It was placed just below the cockpit on the Bf 109 E models in service at the time, and was not renewed when the group was later equipped with the Fw 190.
<French>: Emblème du 4e groupe, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 26. L'emblème représente une tête de tigre, arborant une expression compliquée. Comme le marquage était complexe, la qualité de la tête de tigre différait considérablement d'un avion à l'autre. Il était placé juste en dessous du cockpit de Bf 109 modèle E en service à ce moment là, et il n'a pas été repris quand le groupe a été équipé avec le Fw 190.
<Italian>: Stemma del 4° Gruppo, Jagdgeschwader (Stormo Caccia) 26. Lo stemma ritrae la testa di una tigre con una complicata espressione. Siccome lo stemma era abbastanza intricato, la qualità della testa della tigre differiva sostanzialmente da aereo ad aereo. Era posta appena sotto la cabina di pilotaggio dei Bf 109 in servizio all'epoca e non venne riproposto quando il gruppo venne equipaggiato più tardi con gli Fw190.
<German>: Abzeichen der 4. Stafel des Jagdgeschwaders 26. Das Abzeichen stellt den Kopf eines Tigers dar, der einen verwirrten Ausdruck trägt. Da die Markierung recht kompliziert war, unterschied sich die Qualität des Tigerkopfes von Flugzeug zu Flugzeug erheblich. Bei den damals im Einsatz befindlichen Bf 109 E befand er sich direkt unterhalb des Cockpits und wurde bei der späteren Ausrüstung mit der Fw 190 nicht mehr erneuert.
<Spanish>: Emblema del 4º Grupo, Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 26. El emblema representa la cabeza de un tigre, con una expresión complicada. Como el marcado era bastante intrincado, la calidad de la cabeza de tigre difería sustancialmente de un avión a otro. Se colocó justo debajo de la cabina en los modelos Bf 109 E en servicio en aquella época, y no se renovó cuando el grupo se equipó posteriormente con el Fw 190.
<Polish>: Emblemat 4. Grupy, Jagdgeschwader 26. Emblemat przedstawia głowę tygrysa o skomplikowanym wyrazie twarzy. Ze względu na szczegółowość znaku, jakość wizerunku głowy tygrysa różniła się znacznie w zależności od samolotu. Był umieszczony tuż pod kabiną na modelach Bf 109 E w służbie w tym czasie i nie był odnawiany, gdy grupa otrzymała później Fw 190.
<Czech>: Emblém 4. skupiny, Jagdgeschwader (Stíhací křídlo) 26. Znak zobrazuje hlavu tygra se složitým výrazem. Vzhledem k tomu, že značení bylo poměrně složité, kvalita hlavy tygra se u jednotlivých letounů značně lišila. Na modelech Bf 109 E, které byly v té době ve službě, byl umístěn těsně pod pilotní kabinou a při pozdějším vybavení skupiny letouny Fw 190 již nebyl obnoven.
<Turkish>: Emblem of 4th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 26. The emblem depicts the head of a tiger, sporting a complicated expression. As the marking was quite intricate, the quality of the Tiger’s head differed substantially from aircraft to aircraft. It was placed just below the cockpit on the Bf 109 E models in service at the time, and was not renewed when the group was later equipped with the Fw 190.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 26 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t第 4 大\t队\t徽\t标。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t为\t一\t个\t神\t情\t复\t杂\t的\t老\t虎\t头。\t由\t于\t图\t案\t本\t身\t花\t样\t繁\t多，\t因\t此\t每\t一\t架\t战\t机\t上\t绘\t制\t的\t虎\t头\t图\t案\t几\t乎\t是\t天\t差\t地\t别。\t该\t徽\t标\t见\t于\t第 4 大\t队\t当\t时\t装\t备\t的 Bf 109E 战\t机\t座\t舱\t盖\t下\t方，\t但\t部\t队\t在\t换\t装 Fw 190 后\t并\t没\t有\t继\t续\t为\t新\t战\t机\t绘\t制\t该\t徽\t标。

<TChinese>: Quân huy của Nhóm thứ 4, Jagdgeschwader (Phi đội chiến đấu cơ) 26. Quân huy thể hiện đầu của một con hổ, với biểu cảm phức tạp. Vì hình vẽ khá phức tạp nên chất lượng của đầu Hổ khác biệt đáng kể giữa các máy bay. Nó được đặt ngay bên dưới buồng lái trên các mẫu Bf 109 E đang hoạt động vào thời điểm đó, và không được thay mới khi nhóm sau này được trang bị những chiếc Fw 190.
<HChinese>: 第 26 戰鬥機聯隊第 4 大隊徽標。徽標主體為一個神情複雜的老虎頭。由於圖案本身花樣繁多，因此每一架戰機上繪製的虎頭圖案幾乎是天差地別。該徽標見於第 4 大隊當時裝備的 Bf 109E 戰機座艙蓋下方，但部隊在換裝 Fw 190 後並沒有繼續為新戰機繪製該徽標。
<Comments>: Emblem of 4th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 26. The emblem depicts the head of a tiger, sporting a complicated expression. As the marking was quite intricate, the quality of the Tiger’\ts head differed substantially from aircraft to aircraft. It was placed just below the cockpit on the Bf 109 E models in service at the time, and was not renewed when the group was later equipped with the Fw 190.

<Chinese>: 第 898 海\t航\t中\t队\t“飞\t鱼”\t徽\t标
<TChinese>: Huy hiệu 'Flying Fish', Sư đoàn Không quân Hải quân 898

<English>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. It prominently features a flying fish silhouetted against the sun — like many emblems of this kind it was directly inspired by the badge of the squadron, which displays the same motif. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.
<French>: Emblème du 898e Escadron aéronaval. Comme de nombreux emblèmes de ce type, il s'inspire directement de l'insigne de l'escadron, qui présente le même motif. Ces emblèmes étaient placés sur le côté du nez ou à côté du cockpit des chasseurs à réaction Sea Hawk en service au sein de l'escadron dans les années 1950.
<Italian>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. It prominently features a flying fish silhouetted against the sun — like many emblems of this kind it was directly inspired by the badge of the squadron, which displays the same motif. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.
<German>: "Fliegender Fisch"-Abzeichen, No. 898 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón Aeronaval 898. Como muchos emblemas de este tipo, se inspiró directamente en la insignia del escuadrón, que muestra el mismo motivo. Estos emblemas se colocaban a un lado del morro o junto a la cabina en los cazas a reacción Sea Hawk en servicio con el escuadrón en la década de 1950.
<Russian>: Эмблема "Летучая рыба", 898-я эскадрилья морской авиации королевского флота Британии
<Polish>: Emblemat 898 Naval Air Squadron. Wyraźnie przedstawia latającą rybę na tle słońca - jak wiele takich emblematów, był bezpośrednio inspirowany odznaką dywizjonu, która przedstawia ten sam motyw. Te emblematy były umieszczane z boku nosa lub obok kabiny samolotów Sea Hawk w służbie dywizjonu w latach 50.
<Czech>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. It prominently features a flying fish silhouetted against the sun — like many emblems of this kind it was directly inspired by the badge of the squadron, which displays the same motif. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.
<Turkish>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. It prominently features a flying fish silhouetted against the sun — like many emblems of this kind it was directly inspired by the badge of the squadron, which displays the same motif. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t海\t军\t舰\t队\t航\t空\t兵\t第 989 海\t航\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t与\t许\t多\t同\t类\t标\t识\t一\t样，\t该\t徽\t标\t也\t直\t接\t取\t材\t自\t中\t队\t的\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t样\t式，\t描\t绘\t有\t同\t款\t“飞\t鱼\t映\t日”\t图\t案。\t该\t标\t识\t主\t要\t见\t于\t中\t队\t在 20 世\t纪 50 年\t代\t期\t间\t装\t备\t的\t“海\t鹰”\t喷\t气\t式\t战\t斗\t机，\t喷\t绘\t于\t机\t头\t侧\t面\t或\t驾\t驶\t舱\t旁\t的\t蒙\t皮\t位\t置。
<Japanese>: "Flying Fish" emblem, No. 898 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Portuguese>: Emblema "Flying Fish", No. 898 Esquadrão Aéreo Naval, Braço Aéreo da Frota da Royal Navy
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 898-ї морської авіаескадрильї. На ній помітно зображений силует летючої риби на фоні сонця — як і багато інших емблем такого роду, він був безпосередньо натхненний значком ескадрильї, який відображає той самий мотив. Ці емблеми розміщувалися збоку від носа або поруч із кабіною на реактивних винищувачах Sea Hawk, які перебували на озброєнні ескадрильї в 1950-х роках.
<Serbian>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. It prominently features a flying fish silhouetted against the sun — like many emblems of this kind it was directly inspired by the badge of the squadron, which displays the same motif. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Haditengerészeti Légierő 898. haditengerészeti repülőszázadának emblémája.
<Korean>: 제898해군항공대의 엠블럼입니다. 태양을 등진 채 날아가는 물고기가 눈에 띄는데, 다른 엠블럼들과 유사한 비행대 배지에서 직접 영감을 받아 제작된 것이라고 합니다. 이 엠블럼은 1950년대에 비행대에 배치된 시 호크 제트 전투기의 기수 측면이나 조종석 옆에 사용되었습니다.
<Belarusian>: "Flying Fish" emblem, No. 898 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Romanian>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. It prominently features a flying fish silhouetted against the sun — like many emblems of this kind it was directly inspired by the badge of the squadron, which displays the same motif. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn Không quân Hải quân 898. Nó nổi bật với hình dáng của một con cá bay được đặt trước ánh mặt trời - giống như nhiều biểu tượng của loại này, nó được trực tiếp lấy cảm hứng từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn, hiển thị cùng một biểu tượng. Những biểu tượng này được đặt bên cạnh mũi hoặc bên cạnh buồng lái trên các máy bay tiêm kích Sea Hawk phục vụ với sư đoàn vào những năm 1950.
<HChinese>: 英國皇家海軍艦隊航空兵，第 898 海航中隊“飛魚”徽標
<Comments>: An emblem of 898 Naval Air Squadron. These emblems were placed to the side of the nose or next to the cockpit on the Sea Hawk jet fighters in service with the squadron in the 1950s.

<Chinese>: 第 51 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t“眼\t睛”\t徽\t标
<HChinese>: 第 51 戰鬥機聯隊“眼睛”徽標

<English>: A personal marking of Bf 109 G-6 "White 7", Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 51. Only utilized on one aircraft, a pair of green eyes were painted on the machine gun bulges on either side of the nose, an incidental yet effective position for such markings.
<French>: Un marquage personnel du Bf 109 G-6 "White 7", Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 51. Seulement utilisé sur un seul avion, une paire d'yeux verts sont peint sur les saillants de mitrailleuse de chaque côté du nez, une position accessoire mais efficace pour ces marquages.
<Italian>: Marchio personale del Bf 109G-6 "Bianco 7", Jagdgeschwader (Stormo caccia) 51. Venne usato solo su un aereo, un paio di occhi verdi vennero verniciati sulle bugne delle mitragliatrici ai lati del muso, una posizione molto d'effetto per questo stemma.
<German>: Eine persönliche Kennzeichnung der Bf 109 G-6 "Weiße 7", Jagdgeschwader 51. Nur auf einem Flugzeug verwendet, wurden ein Paar grüne Augen auf die Maschinengewehrwülste auf beiden Seiten der Nase gemalt, eine zufällige, aber effektive Position für solche Markierungen.
<Spanish>: Una marca personal del Bf 109 G-6 "Blanco 7", Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 51. Utilizado sólo en un avión, se pintaron un par de ojos verdes en las protuberancias de las ametralladoras a ambos lados del morro, una posición incidental pero eficaz para tales marcas.
<Polish>: Osobiste oznaczenie Bf 109 G-6 "Biała 7", Jagdgeschwader (Skrzydło Myśliwskie) 51. Użyte tylko na jednym samolocie, para zielonych oczu została namalowana na wybrzuszeniach karabinów maszynowych po obu stronach nosa, co było przypadkowym, ale skutecznym miejscem na takie oznaczenie.
<Czech>: Osobní označení Bf 109 G-6 "Bílá 7", Jagdgeschwader (Stíhací křídlo) 51. Používalo se pouze na jednom letounu, dvojice zelených očí byla namalována na kulometné výduti po obou stranách přídě, což je náhodné, ale účinné místo pro takové označení.
<Turkish>: A personal marking of Bf 109 G-6 "White 7", Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 51. Only utilized on one aircraft, a pair of green eyes were painted on the machine gun bulges on either side of the nose, an incidental yet effective position for such markings.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 51 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t所\t属 Bf 109 G-6\t“白 7”\t战\t机\t涂\t布\t的\t个\t人\t徽\t标。\t该\t徽\t标\t仅\t见\t于\t这\t一\t战\t机，\t图\t样\t为\t涂\t布\t在\t机\t鼻\t机\t枪\t鼓\t包\t上\t的\t一\t双\t绿\t色\t眼\t睛。\t尽\t管\t可\t能\t并\t非\t刻\t意\t为\t之，\t其\t独\t特\t外\t观\t依\t旧\t令\t人\t印\t象\t深\t刻。
<Japanese>: A personal marking of Bf 109 G-6 "White 7", Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 51. Only utilized on one aircraft, a pair of green eyes were painted on the machine gun bulges on either side of the nose, an incidental yet effective position for such markings.

<Romanian>: A personal marking of Bf 109 G-6 "White 7", Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 51. Only utilized on one aircraft, a pair of green eyes were painted on the machine gun bulges on either side of the nose, an incidental yet effective position for such markings.

<Chinese>: 第 10 快\t速\t轰\t炸\t机\t联\t队\t第 3 大\t队\t徽\t标
<HChinese>: 第 10 快速轟炸機聯隊第 3 大隊徽標

<English>: The emblem of 3rd Group, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Fast-Bomber Wing) 10. The emblem depicts a silver winged arrow, representative of the role of the unit. The emblem was in use with Fw 190 A units operating in Tunisia in 1943, with the emblem being placed on the side of the nose.
<French>: L'emblème du 3e groupe, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Fast-Bomber Wing) 10. L'emblème représente une flèche d'argent ailée, représentative du rôle de l'unité. L'emblème était en usage sur les unités de Fw 190 A opérant en Tunisie en 1943, avec l'emblème placé de chaque côté du nez.
<Italian>: Stemma del 3° gruppo, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Stormo Bombardieri Veloci) 10. Raffigura una freccia argentata alata, rappresentante il ruolo dell'unità. Lo stemma era usato sulle unità di Fw 190 A operanti in Tunisia nel 1943, con lo stemma piazzato sul lato del muso.
<German>: Das Abzeichen der 3. Gruppe des Schnellkampfgeschwaders 10. Das Abzeichen zeigt einen silbernen, geflügelten Pfeil, der für die Aufgabe der Einheit steht. Das Abzeichen wurde 1943 bei den in Tunesien eingesetzten Fw 190 A-Einheiten verwendet, wobei das Abzeichen seitlich an der Nase angebracht war.
<Spanish>: Emblema del 3º Grupo, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Ala de Bombarderos Rápidos) 10. El emblema representa una flecha alada plateada, representativa del papel de la unidad. El emblema se utilizaba en las unidades de Fw 190 A que operaban en Túnez en 1943, con el emblema colocado en el lateral del morro.
<Polish>: Emblemat 3. Grupy, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Szybkie Skrzydło Bombowe) 10. Emblemat przedstawia srebrną skrzydlatą strzałę, reprezentującą rolę jednostki. Emblemat był używany przez jednostki Fw 190 A operujące w Tunezji w 1943 roku, z emblematem umieszczonym na boku nosa.
<Czech>: Emblém 3. skupiny, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Rychlé bombardovací křídlo) 10. Znak zobrazuje stříbrný okřídlený šíp, který reprezentuje úlohu jednotky. Znak byl používán u jednotek Fw 190 A působících v Tunisku v roce 1943, přičemž emblém byl umístěn na boku přídě.
<Turkish>: The emblem of 3rd Group, Schnellkampfgeschwader (Fast-Bomber Wing) 10. The emblem depicts a silver winged arrow, representative of the role of the unit. The emblem was in use with Fw 190 A units operating in Tunisia in 1943, with the emblem being placed on the side of the nose.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 10 快\t速\t轰\t炸\t机\t联\t队\t第 3 大\t队\t徽\t标。\t图\t案\t主\t体\t为\t一\t支\t银\t色\t的\t带\t翼\t飞\t箭，\t象\t征\t着\t该\t联\t队\t的\t战\t术\t定\t位。\t该\t徽\t标\t见\t于 1943 年\t驻\t扎\t在\t突\t尼\t斯\t战\t区\t的 Fw 190A 单\t位，\t通\t常\t涂\t布\t在\t机\t鼻\t侧\t面。

<English>: The main emblem of Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 3. The emblem features a winged letter U after the group’s namesake, which it adopted in late 1941. In addition to specific group markings, this emblem appeared on the nose of several later aircraft operated by the group, including F and G models of the Bf 109, and late Fw 190 variants.
<French>: Le principal emblème du Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 3. L'emblème comporte une lettre U ailée d'après l'homonyme du groupe qu'il l'a adopté à la fin de 1941. En plus des marquages spécifiques du groupe, cet emblème apparait sur le nez de plusieurs appareils tardifs opérant dans le groupe, incluant les modèles F et G du Bf 109 et des variantes tardif du Fw 190.
<Italian>: Stemma dello Jagdgeschwader (Stormo Caccia) 3. Rafficurava una lettera U alata dopo il nome del gruppo, adottato nel tardo 1941. Oltre agli stemmi specifici del gruppo, questo emblema appariva sul muso di vari aerei adottati successivamente dal gruppo, inclusi i modelli F e G dei Bf 109 e le versioni più moderne di Fw 190.
<German>: Das Hauptabzeichen des Jagdgeschwaders 3. Das Abzeichen zeigt ein geflügeltes U nach dem Namensgeber der Gruppe, das sie Ende 1941 übernahm. Zusätzlich zu den spezifischen Gruppenabzeichen erschien dieses Abzeichen auf der Nase mehrerer späterer Flugzeuge, die von dem Geschwader verwendet wurden, darunter F- und G-Modelle der Bf 109 und späte Fw 190-Varianten.
<Spanish>: Emblema principal de la Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 3. El emblema presenta una letra U alada en honor al homónimo del grupo, que adoptó a finales de 1941. Además de las marcas específicas del grupo, este emblema apareció en el morro de varios aviones posteriores operados por el grupo, incluidos los modelos F y G del Bf 109, y las últimas variantes del Fw 190.
<Polish>: Główny emblemat Jagdgeschwader 3. Emblemat przedstawia skrzydlatą literę U nawiązującą do patrona grupy, którą przyjęła pod koniec 1941 roku. Oprócz specyficznych oznaczeń grupowych, ten emblemat pojawiał się na nosie kilku późniejszych samolotów operowanych przez grupę, w tym modeli F i G Bf 109 oraz późnych wersji Fw 190.
<Czech>: Hlavní emblém Jagdgeschwader (Stíhacího křídla) 3. Znak tvoří okřídlené písmeno U podle názvu skupiny, který přijala koncem roku 1941. Kromě specifického označení skupiny se tento znak objevil na přídi několika pozdějších letounů provozovaných skupinou, včetně modelů F a G Bf 109 a pozdních variant Fw 190.

<English>: Emblem of 2nd Group, Kampfgeschwader (Tactical Wing) 30. A black swooping eagle on a red shield, indicative of the nickname of the unit. The group almost exclusively operated Ju 88 bombers, with the emblem being placed under the front of the cockpit.
<French>: Emblème du 2e groupe, Kampfgeschwader (Tactical Wing) 30. Un aigle noir plongeant sur un bouclier rouge, révélateur du surnom de l'unité. Le groupe opérait presque exclusivement sur bombardier Ju 88, avec l'emblème placé sous l'avant du cockpit.
<Italian>: Stemma del 2° Gruppo, Kampfgeschwader (Stormo Tattico) 30. Un'aqulia nera su uno scudo rosso, indicante il nomignolo dell'unità. Il gruppo operò quasi esclusivamente con i bombardieri Ju 88, lo stemma era posto sotto la parte frontale della cabina di pilotaggio.
<German>: Abzeichen der 2. Gruppe des Kampfgeschwaders 30. Ein schwarzer Adler im Sturzflug auf einem roten Schild, was auf den Spitznamen der Einheit hinweist. Die Gruppe setzte fast ausschließlich Ju-88-Bomber ein, wobei das Abzeichen unter der Vorderseite des Cockpits angebracht war.
<Spanish>: Emblema del 2º Grupo, Kampfgeschwader (Ala Táctica) 30. Un águila negra en picado sobre un escudo rojo, indicativo del apodo de la unidad. El grupo operaba casi exclusivamente bombarderos Ju 88, y el emblema se colocaba bajo la parte delantera de la cabina.
<Polish>: Emblemat 2. Grupy, Kampfgeschwader (Skrzydło Taktyczne) 30. Czarny orzeł w locie na czerwonej tarczy, wskazujący na przydomek jednostki. Grupa prawie wyłącznie operowała bombowcami Ju 88, z emblematem umieszczonym pod przodem kabiny.
<Czech>: Emblém 2. skupiny, Kampfgeschwader (taktické křídlo) 30. Černý stoupající orel na červeném štítu, který označuje přezdívku jednotky. Skupina téměř výhradně provozovala bombardéry Ju 88, přičemž znak byl umístěn pod přední částí kokpitu.

<English>: The roundel of No. 31 Squadron. These special squadron specific roundels were derived from the squadron badge, No. 31 featured a gold star in a verdant wreath, and these colors transferred over to the checkerboard flash. The roundel additionally retained the star in the middle, a common motif of the squadron that manifested repeatedly throughout their group, even in their nickname — the "Goldstars". These roundels were found on the Tornado aircraft they operated, and could be seen under the front-side window of the cockpit.
<French>: La cocarde de l'Escadron n° 31. Ces cocardes spécifiques aux escadrons étaient dérivées de l'insigne de l'escadron. L'Escadron n° 31 comportait une étoile d'or dans une couronne de verdure, et ces couleurs ont été transposées sur le damier flash. La cocarde conservait en outre l'étoile au milieu, un motif commun à l'escadron qui se manifestait de façon répétée dans tout le groupe, même dans son surnom - les "Goldstars". Ces cocardes se trouvaient sur les Tornado qu'ils pilotaient et étaient visibles sous le hublot avant du cockpit.
<Italian>: The roundel of No. 31 Squadron. These special squadron specific roundels were derived from the squadron badge, No. 31 featured a gold star in a verdant wreath, and these colors transferred over to the checkerboard flash. The roundel additionally retained the star in the middle, a common motif of the squadron that manifested repeatedly throughout their group, even in their nickname — the "Goldstars". These roundels were found on the Tornado aircraft they operated, and could be seen under the front-side window of the cockpit.
<German>: Abzeichen des 31st Squadron auf Untergrund, RAF
<Spanish>: Escarapela del Escuadrón No. 31. Estas escarapelas especiales específicas del escuadrón se derivaban de la insignia del escuadrón, en la que el No. 31 presentaba una estrella dorada en una corona verde, y estos colores se transfirieron al destello en forma de damero. Además, la escarapela conservaba la estrella en el centro, un motivo común del escuadrón que se manifestaba repetidamente en todo su grupo, incluso en su apodo: las "Estrellas Doradas". Estas escarapelas se encontraban en los aviones Tornado que operaban, y podían verse bajo la ventanilla frontal de la cabina.
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry nr 31. Te specjalne emblematy eskadr były inspirowane ich odznakami. Emblemat Eskadry nr 31 przedstawiał złotą gwiazdę w zielonym wieńcu, a te kolory zostały przeniesione na szachownicę. Emblemat dodatkowo zachował gwiazdę w środku, co było częstym motywem eskadry, widocznym nawet w ich pseudonimie — "Goldstars" (Złote Gwiazdy). Te emblematy znajdowały się na samolotach Tornado, którymi operowali, i można je było zobaczyć pod przednim oknem kokpitu.

Рондель додатково зберіг зірку в середині, загальний мотив ескадрильї, який неодноразово проявлявся в їхній групі, навіть у їхньому прізвиську — «Золоті зірки». <English>: The roundel of No. 54 Squadron. Like all squadron specific roundels this flash is derivative of the main squadron badge, maintaining the blue and gold colors from the main emblem — a blue rampant lion adorned with fleur-de-lis. A simplified version of this lion makes it into the squadron roundel as well. This marking was positioned on the side of the nose on the Hawker Hunters in operation with the squadron in the late 1960s.
<French>: La cocarde de l'Escadron n° 54. Comme toutes les cocardes spécifiques à un escadron, cette cocarde est dérivée de l'insigne principal de l'escadron, conservant les couleurs bleu et or de l'emblème principal - un lion bleu rampant orné de fleurs de lys. Une version simplifiée de ce lion figure également dans la cocarde de l'escadron. Ce marquage était placé sur le côté du nez des Hawker Hunter utilisés par l'escadron à la fin des années 1960.

Una versión simplificada de este león aparece también en la escarapela del escuadrón. Esta marca se colocó en el lateral del morro de los Hawker Hunter en servicio con el escuadrón a finales de los años 60.

Uproszczona wersja tego lwa pojawia się także w kokardzie dywizjonu. To oznaczenie znajdowało się na boku nosa samolotów Hawker Hunter operujących w dywizjonie pod koniec lat 60.

<English>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<French>: Emblème de la 702e Escadrille aéronavale. La 702 a été formée le 16 juillet 1936, et pendant la majeure partie de sa vie opérationnelle, elle a piloté divers avions de reconnaissance. Après avoir été réformée en 1978, elle a servi d'unité d'entraînement pour l'exploitation et la maintenance du Westland Lynx, avant d'être absorbée par le 815 NAS en 2014. Le marquage est la tête stylisée d'un Lynx, dérivé de l'insigne de l'escadron. Le marquage a été placé sur plusieurs de leurs hélicoptères Lynx, et a été positionné à droite de la fenêtre latérale.
<Italian>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<German>: "Luchs"-Abzeichen, No. 815 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón Aeronaval 702. El 702 se formó el 16 de Julio de 1936, y durante la mayor parte de su vida operativa temprana voló con varios aviones de reconocimiento. Tras ser reformado en 1978, sirvió como unidad de entrenamiento operando y manteniendo el Westland Lynx, antes de ser absorbido por el 815 NAS en 2014. La marca es la cabeza estilizada de un Lince, derivada de la insignia del escuadrón. El distintivo se colocó en varios de sus helicópteros Lynx, a la derecha de la ventanilla lateral.
<Russian>: Эмблема "Рысь", 815 эскадрилья ВВС Королевского флота Британии
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry Lotnictwa Morskiego nr 702. Eskadra została sformowana 16 lipca 1936 roku i przez większość wczesnego okresu operacyjnego latała na różnych samolotach rozpoznawczych. Po ponownym sformowaniu w 1978 roku służyła jako jednostka szkoleniowa, obsługując i utrzymując śmigłowce Westland Lynx, zanim została wchłonięta przez Eskadrę 815 NAS w 2014 roku. Emblematem była stylizowana głowa rysia, wywodząca się z herbu eskadry. Znak ten był umieszczany na kilku śmigłowcach Lynx, znajdując się po prawej stronie okna bocznego.
<Czech>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<Turkish>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t海\t军\t舰\t队\t航\t空\t兵\t第 702 海\t航\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t第 702 海\t航\t中\t队\t成\t立\t于 1936 年 7 月 16 日，\t早\t期\t主\t要\t装\t备\t各\t型\t侦\t察\t机\t执\t行\t侦\t查\t任\t务。\t中\t队\t于 1978 年\t重\t组\t为\t训\t练\t单\t位，\t主\t要\t装\t备\t韦\t斯\t特\t兰\t“山\t猫”\t直\t升\t机，\t随\t后\t在 2014 年\t并\t入\t第 815 海\t航\t中\t队。\t徽\t标\t采\t用\t了\t中\t队\t纹\t章\t图\t样\t中\t标\t志\t性\t的\t山\t猫\t头\t为\t主\t体，\t主\t要\t见\t于\t部\t队\t下\t属\t“山\t猫”\t直\t升\t机\t的\t机\t身\t舷\t窗\t右\t侧。
<Japanese>: "Lynx" emblem, No. 815 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Portuguese>: Emblema "Lynx", No. 815 Esquadrão Aéreo Naval, Frota Aérea da Marinha Real
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 702-ї морської авіаційної ескадрильї. 702-а була сформований 16-го липня 1936 року, і протягом більшої частини свого раннього терміну служби літала на різних літаках-розвідниках. Після реформування в 1978 році вони слугували навчальним підрозділом, який керував і обслуговував Westland Lynx, перш ніж увійти до складу 815 NAS у 2014 році. Позначкою є стилізована голова рисі, похідна від значка ескадрильї. Маркування було розміщено на кількох їхніх вертольотах Lynx праворуч від бічного вікна.
<Serbian>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Haditengerészeti Légierő 815. haditengerészeti repülőszázadának emblémája.
<Korean>: 제702해군항공비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 1936년 7월 16일에 창설된 이 비행대는 초기에 다양한 정찰기를 운용하였습니다. 1978년에 재편성된 이 비행대는 웨스트랜드 링스를 운용하는 훈련대로 편성되어 있다가 2014년, 제815비행대와 통합되었습니다. 이곳은 비행대의 배지에서 파생된 스라소니(Lynx)의 머리가 마킹되어 있었습니다. 해당 마킹은 수 대의 링스 헬리콥터의  우측면 창문에 적용되어 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: "Lynx" emblem, No. 815 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Romanian>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn Không quân Hải quân 702. Sư đoàn 702 được thành lập vào ngày 16 tháng 7 năm 1936, và trong phần lớn thời kỳ hoạt động đầu của nó, họ đã sử dụng nhiều loại máy bay trinh sát khác nhau. Sau khi tái hình thành vào năm 1978, họ phục vụ như một đơn vị đào tạo vận hành và bảo dưỡng máy bay Westland Lynx, trước khi được hợp nhất vào Sư đoàn Không quân Hải quân 815 vào năm 2014. Biểu tượng là hình đầu của một con Linh, phát triển từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn. Biểu tượng này được đặt trên một số trực thăng Lynx của họ, và được đặt bên phải của cửa sổ bên.
<HChinese>: 英國皇家海軍艦隊航空兵，第 815 海航中隊“山貓”徽標
<Comments>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.

<English>: Emblem of 1st Group, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Long Range Reconnaissance Group) 120. The emblem displays the skull of a Moose with the distinctive thick antlers. A simplification of the original emblem, this marking was painted to the side of the nose on the Ju 88 aircraft in use with the group, just in front of the cockpit.
<French>: Emblème du 1e groupe, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (groupe de reconnaissance à longue portée) 120. L'emblème affiche le crane d'un élan avec les épais bois distinctifs. Une simplification de l'emblème original, ce marquage était peint sur le côté du nez des avions Ju 88 en usage dans le groupe, juste devant le cockpit.
<Italian>: Stemma del 1° Gruppo Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Gruppo di Ricognizione a Lungo Raggio) 120. Lo stemma rappresentava un teschio di alce con le corna spesse. Una semplificazione dello stemma originale che veniva dipinto sui lati del muso dei Ju 88 operativi nel gruppo, appena avanti alla cabina di pilotaggio.
<German>: Abzeichen der 1. Staffel, Fernaufklärungsgruppe 120. Das Abzeichen zeigt den Schädel eines Elches mit dem charakteristischen dicken Geweih. Dieses Abzeichen, das eine Vereinfachung des ursprünglichen Abzeichens darstellt, wurde seitlich auf die Nase der bei der Gruppe eingesetzten Ju 88-Flugzeuge gemalt, direkt vor dem Cockpit.
<Spanish>: Emblema del 1º Grupo, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Grupo de Reconocimiento de Largo Alcance) 120. El emblema muestra el cráneo de un alce con la gruesa cornamenta distintiva. Esta marca, simplificación del emblema original, se pintó en el morro de los aviones Ju 88 del grupo, justo delante de la cabina.
<Polish>: Emblemat 1. Grupy, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Grupa Rozpoznania Dalekiego Zasięgu) 120. Emblemat przedstawia czaszkę łosia z charakterystycznymi grubymi porożami. Jest to uproszczenie oryginalnego emblematu, który był malowany na boku nosa samolotów Ju 88 używanych przez grupę, tuż przed kabiną.
<Czech>: Emblém 1. skupiny Fernaufklärungsgruppe (průzkumná skupina s dlouhým doletem) 120. Znak zobrazuje lebku losa s charakteristickým hustým parožím. Toto označení, které je zjednodušením původního znaku, bylo na letounech Ju 88 používaných u skupiny namalováno na boční stranu přídě, těsně před pilotní kabinu.
<Turkish>: Emblem of 1st Group, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Long Range Reconnaissance Group) 120. The emblem displays the skull of a Moose with the distinctive thick antlers. A simplification of the original emblem, this marking was painted to the side of the nose on the Ju 88 aircraft in use with the group, just in front of the cockpit.

<Chinese>: 第 400 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t第 7 中\t队\t徽\t标
<HChinese>: 第 400 戰鬥機聯隊第 7 中隊徽標

<English>: An emblem used by 7th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Like several late-war markings this emblem was never officially approved to represent 7th group, but was nevertheless placed on the nose of their Me 163 fighters. The emblem depicts Baron Münchhausen riding a bottle rocket, making it quite an appropriate motif.
<French>: Un emblème utilisé par le 7e groupe, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Comme plusieurs marquages tardifs de la guerre, cet emblème n'était jamais approuvé officiellement pour représenter le 7e groupe, mais était néanmoins placé sur le nez de leurs chasseurs Me 163. L'emblème représente le Baron Münchhausen chevauchant une bouteille-roquette, ce qui en fait un motif tout à fait approprié.
<Italian>: Uno stemma usato dal 7° gruppo, Jagdgeschwader (Stormo Caccia) 400. Come molti altri stemmi di tardo conflitto, questo non venne mai ufficialmente approvato per rappresentare il 7° gruppo ma posto sotto il muso dei loro caccia Me 163. Raffigurava il Barone Münchhausen che cavalcava un razzo facendolo apparire come inappropriato.
<German>: Ein Abzeichen, das von der 7. Staffel des Jagdgeschwaders 400 verwendet wurde. Wie viele andere Abzeichen aus der späten Phase des Krieges wurde auch dieses Abzeichen nie offiziell für die 7. Staffel genehmigt, wurde aber dennoch auf der Nase ihrer Me 163-Jagdflugzeuge angebracht. Das Abzeichen zeigt Baron Münchhausen, der auf einer Flaschenrakete reitet, und ist damit ein recht passendes Motiv.
<Spanish>: Emblema utilizado por el 7º Grupo, Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 400. Al igual que varias marcas de finales de la guerra, este emblema nunca fue aprobado oficialmente para representar al 7º grupo, pero sin embargo se colocó en el morro de sus cazas Me 163. El emblema representa al Barón Münchhausen montado en una botella cohete, lo que lo convierte en un motivo bastante apropiado.
<Polish>: Emblemat używany przez 7. Grupę, Jagdgeschwader (Skrzydło Myśliwskie) 400. Jak wiele oznaczeń z końca wojny, ten emblemat nigdy nie został oficjalnie zatwierdzony do reprezentowania 7. Grupy, ale mimo to umieszczano go na nosach ich myśliwców Me 163. Emblemat przedstawia Barona Münchhausena jadącego na butelkowej rakiecie, co jest dość trafnym motywem.
<Czech>: Emblém používaný 7. skupinou, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Stejně jako několik dalších pozdně válečných označení nebyl tento znak nikdy oficiálně schválen pro reprezentaci 7. skupiny, přesto byl umístěn na přídi jejich stíhaček Me 163. Znak zobrazuje barona Prášila jedoucího na raketě z láhve, což z něj činí docela vhodný motiv.
<Turkish>: An emblem used by 7th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Like several late-war markings this emblem was never officially approved to represent 7th group, but was nevertheless placed on the nose of their Me 163 fighters. The emblem depicts Baron Münchhausen riding a bottle rocket, making it quite an appropriate motif.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 400 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t第 7 中\t队\t徽\t标。\t与\t战\t争\t末\t期\t设\t计\t的\t多\t数\t部\t队\t标\t识\t一\t样，\t该\t徽\t标\t从\t未\t获\t得\t官\t方\t正\t式\t采\t纳，\t不\t过\t第 7 中\t队\t的 Me 163 战\t斗\t机\t依\t旧\t在\t机\t鼻\t部\t位\t涂\t有\t该\t徽\t标。\t该\t标\t识\t主\t体\t为\t骑\t着\t酒\t瓶\t作\t为\t火\t箭\t的\t闵\t希\t豪\t森\t男\t爵，\t对\t于\t一\t支\t装\t备\t火\t箭\t战\t斗\t机\t的\t部\t队\t而\t言\t的\t确\t恰\t如\t其\t分。

<English>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<French>: Un emblème de l'Escadron n° 11. Inspiré de l'insigne de l'escadron, ce marquage représente un couple d'aigles en tandem, en référence au premier avion utilisé par l'escadron - le Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus biplace - les aigles ont été choisis en particulier pour incarner un sens de la force et de la vitesse dans les airs. Ce marquage spécifique n'a été utilisé que plus récemment, sur la dérive des Typhoons en service au sein de l'escadron.
<Italian>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón No. 11. Inspirada en la insignia del escuadrón, esta marca de escudo representa un par de águilas en tándem, una referencia al primer avión operado por el escuadrón -el Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus biplaza - las águilas fueron elegidas en particular para encarnar una sensación de fuerza y velocidad en el aire. Esta marca específica se ha empezado a utilizar más recientemente, y se encuentra en el estabilizador vertical de los Typhoons en servicio con el escuadrón.
<Polish>: Emblemat 11 Dywizjonu. Zainspirowany odznaką dywizjonu, ten herb przedstawia parę orłów w tandemie, co odnosi się do pierwszego samolotu operowanego przez dywizjon - dwumiejscowego Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus. Orły zostały wybrane, aby ucieleśnić siłę i szybkość w powietrzu. Ten konkretny znak jest używany od stosunkowo niedawna, znajdując się na pionowym stateczniku Typhoonów w służbie dywizjonu.
<Czech>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Turkish>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 11 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t该\t盾\t徽\t取\t材\t自\t中\t队\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t图\t样，\t描\t绘\t了\t一\t对\t并\t列\t的\t雄\t鹰\t形\t象，\t象\t征\t着\t部\t队\t装\t备\t的\t首\t款\t战\t机 - 双\t座\t布\t局\t的\t维\t克\t斯 F.B 5\t“空\t中\t炮\t艇”\t战\t斗\t机；\t雄\t鹰\t则\t代\t表\t了\t空\t中\t速\t度\t与\t力\t量\t的\t王\t者，\t彰\t显\t出\t部\t队\t的\t军\t种\t特\t征。\t这\t一\t徽\t标\t最\t近\t才\t投\t入\t使\t用，\t见\t于\t中\t队\t下\t属\t“台\t风”\t战\t机\t的\t垂\t尾\t位\t置。
<Japanese>: Emblem of the 11th Fighter Squadron, RAF
<Portuguese>: Emblema do 11º Esquadrão de Caça, RAF
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 11-ї ескадрильї. Натхненний значком ескадрильї, цей знак на щиті зображує пару орлів у тандемі, відсилання до першого літака ескадрильї — двомісного Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — орли були обрані, зокрема, щоб втілити відчуття сили та швидкості в повітрі. Це специфічне маркування почало використовуватися частіше, його можна знайти на вертикальному стабілізаторі Typhoon, що перебував на озброєнні ескадрильї.
<Serbian>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Hungarian>: A 11. vadászrepülő-század emblémája, brit Királyi Légierő.
<Korean>: 제11비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 비행대의 배지에서 영감을 받은 이 엠블럼은 방패 문양에 한 쌍의 독수리가 나란히 서 있는 모습으로, 비행대가 최초로 운용한 항공기인 2인승 빅커스 F.B 5 건버스를 상징하고 있습니다. 특히, 공중에서의 힘과 속도감을 상징하기 위해 독수리를 채용하고 있었습니다. 이 표식은 최근에 사용되기 시작했으며, 비행대에서 운용 중인 타이푼의 수직 안정판에서 찾아볼 수 있습니다.

<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn số 11. Lấy cảm hứng từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn, biểu tượng hình chiếc khiên này miêu tả một cặp đại bàng song hành, một tượng trưng cho các máy bay đầu tiên được sư đoàn vận hành - máy bay hai chỗ Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus - đại bàng được chọn đặc biệt để tượng trưng cho sức mạnh và tốc độ trong không khí. Biểu tượng cụ thể này chỉ mới được sử dụng gần đây, được tìm thấy trên thân cân bằng dọc của các máy bay Typhoons đang phục vụ với sư đoàn.
<HChinese>: 英國皇家空軍第 11 戰鬥機中隊徽標

<Chinese>: 第 111 飞\t行\t中\t队\t识\t别\t徽\t标
<TChinese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Sư đoàn số 111

<English>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<French>: La cocarde de l'escadron n° 111. La plupart des cocardes d'escadron utilisent une barre en damier avec un emblème au centre, mais l'escadron 111 a opté pour quelque chose d'un peu plus frappant. Ce marquage particulier était apposé sur les McDonnell Douglas Phantoms exploités par l'escadron dans les années 1970. Comme la plupart des emblèmes de ce type, ils étaient placés sur le côté du nez, avec la pointe inférieure vers l'avant.
<Italian>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<German>: Abzeichen des 111th Squadron auf Untergrundstreifen, Leuchars, RAF
<Spanish>: Escarapela del Escuadrón No. 111. La mayoría de las escarapelas de los escuadrones utilizaban una barra en forma de tablero de ajedrez con un emblema en el centro, aunque el No. 111, en este ejemplo, optó por algo un poco más llamativo. Esta marca en particular se colocó en los McDonnell Douglas Phantom operados por el escuadrón en la década de 1970. Como la mayoría de las escarapelas de este tipo, se colocaban a lo largo del morro, con la punta inferior hacia delante.
<Polish>: Kokarda 111 Dywizjonu. Większość kokard dywizjonowych miała szachownicowy pas z emblematem w centrum, jednak 111 Dywizjon w tym przykładzie wybrał coś bardziej uderzającego. To oznaczenie znajdowało się na samolotach McDonnell Douglas Phantom operowanych przez dywizjon w latach 70. Jak większość tego typu kokard, były umieszczone wzdłuż boku nosa, z dolnym punktem skierowanym do przodu.
<Czech>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Turkish>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 111 飞\t行\t中\t队\t识\t别\t徽\t标。\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t识\t别\t条\t带\t大\t多\t采\t用\t棋\t盘\t格\t纹 + 部\t队\t徽\t标\t的\t组\t合，\t而\t第 111 飞\t行\t中\t队\t却\t不\t走\t寻\t常\t路\t采\t用\t了\t更\t具\t视\t觉\t冲\t击\t力\t的\t闪\t电\t图\t案。\t这\t一\t样\t式\t的\t识\t别\t条\t带\t主\t要\t见\t于\t上\t世\t纪 70 年\t代\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t麦\t克\t唐\t纳\t-\t道\t格\t拉\t斯\t“鬼\t怪”\t战\t斗\t机，\t与\t其\t他\t同\t类\t标\t识\t一\t样\t喷\t绘\t在\t机\t鼻\t侧\t面，\t闪\t电\t下\t端\t指\t向\t前\t方。
<Japanese>: Emblem of 111th Squadron flash, Leuchars, RAF
<Portuguese>: Emblema do 111º Esquadrão Flash, Leuchars, RAF
<Ukrainian>: Рондель 111-ї ескадрильї. Більшість ескадрильних ронделів використовували шахову смугу з емблемою в центрі, хоча 111-а у цьому прикладі вибрала щось більш яскраве. Це маркування було розміщене на McDonnell Douglas Phantom, якими керувала ескадрилья в 1970-х роках. Як і більшість ронделів цього типу, вони розташовувалися збоку від носа нижньою точкою вперед.
<Serbian>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Légierő 111. repülőszázadának emblémája. Leuchars, Skócia.
<Korean>: 제111비행대의 라운델입니다. 대다수의 경우 비행대 엠블럼이 중앙에 위치하고, 양 옆으로 체크무늬가 존재했는데, 제111비행대의 경우 더 '독특한' 방향을 선택하였습니다. 이 마킹은 1970년대에 운용했던 맥도넬 더글러스 팬텀에 사용되었으며, 기수 측면에 부착되어 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: Emblem of 111th Squadron flash, Leuchars, RAF
<Romanian>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<TChinese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Sư đoàn số 111. Hầu hết các huy hiệu của các sư đoàn sử dụng một thanh ô vuông kèm theo một biểu tượng ở giữa, tuy nhiên, Sư đoàn số 111 trong ví dụ này đã chọn một điều gì đó nổi bật hơn. Biểu tượng cụ thể này được đặt trên các máy bay McDonnell Douglas Phantoms được sư đoàn vận hành trong những năm 1970. Giống như hầu hết các huy hiệu tròn của loại này, chúng được đặt dọc theo bên của mũi máy bay, với điểm thấp nhất hướng về phía trước.
<HChinese>: 盧赫斯，英國皇家空軍第 111 中隊識別標誌

Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.

<Chinese>: 第 43 飞\t行\t中\t队\t后\t期\t“斗\t鸡”\t徽\t标
<Korean>: 영국 왕립공군 제43비행대(No. 43 Squadron RAF)의 "싸우는 수탉" 엠블럼 (후기형)
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng "Fighting Cock" (bản mới), Sư đoàn số 43

<English>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<French>: Un emblème de l'escadron n° 43. Cet emblème représente un coq de bruyère et a été utilisé au début des années 1970. Le marquage est dérivé de l'insigne de l'escadron qui représente également un coq coloré. Les pilotes de cet escadron ont également utilisé ces oiseaux pour décorer leurs avions pendant la Seconde Guerre mondiale, avec plusieurs variantes connues. Ce marquage particulier se trouvait exclusivement sur les McDonnell Douglas Phantom en service au sein de la 43e escadrille, et était placé sur la dérive.
<Italian>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<German>: Abzeichen des "Kampfhahns", Nr. 43 Squadron, RAF Leuchars, 1978
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón No. 43. Esta marca muestra un gallo de pelea, y empezó a utilizarse a principios de la década de 1970. La marca deriva de la insignia del escuadrón, que también representa un colorido gallo; los pilotos de este escuadrón también utilizaron estas aves para adornar sus aviones en la Segunda Guerra Mundial, con varias variaciones conocidas. Esta marca en particular se encontraba exclusivamente en los McDonnell Douglas Phantom en servicio con el No. 43, y estaba colocada en el estabilizador vertical.
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry nr 43. Ten znak przedstawia bojowego koguta i zaczął być używany na początku lat 70. XX wieku. Emblemat wywodzi się z herbu eskadry, który również przedstawia kolorowego koguta; piloci tej eskadry używali tych ptaków do ozdabiania swoich samolotów podczas II wojny światowej, z kilkoma znanymi wariantami. Ten konkretny emblemat znajdował się wyłącznie na samolotach McDonnell Douglas Phantom w służbie Eskadry nr 43 i był umieszczony na pionowym stabilizatorze.
<Czech>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<Turkish>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 43 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t该\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t图\t案\t为\t源\t自\t部\t队\t纹\t章\t图\t样\t的\t斗\t鸡\t形\t象，\t于\t上\t世\t纪 70 年\t代\t初\t期\t投\t入\t使\t用。\t早\t在\t第\t二\t次\t世\t界\t大\t战\t期\t间，\t来\t自\t第 43 中\t队\t的\t飞\t行\t员\t们\t就\t用\t斗\t鸡\t图\t案\t装\t饰\t自\t己\t的\t战\t机。\t这\t一\t样\t式\t的\t徽\t标\t仅\t见\t于\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t麦\t克\t唐\t纳\t-\t道\t格\t拉\t斯\t“鬼\t怪”\t战\t斗\t机，\t位\t于\t垂\t尾\t部\t位。
<Japanese>: "Fighting Cock" emblem, No. 43 Squadron, RAF Leuchars, 1978
<Portuguese>: Emblema "Fighting Cock", Esquadrão No. 43, RAF Leuchars, 1978
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 43-ї ескадрильї. Це маркування відображає півня і ввійшло в ужиток на початку 1970-х років. Маркування походить від значка ескадрильї, на якому також зображений різнокольоровий півень; Пілоти цієї ескадрильї також використовували цих птахів для прикраси своїх літаків під час Другої світової війни, з кількома відомими варіантами. Це маркування було знайдено виключно на McDonnell Douglas Phantom, які були на озброєнні у 43-ї, і було розташоване на вертикальному стабілізаторі.
<Serbian>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Légierő 43. századának emblémája, Royal Air Force Leuchars (1978).
<Korean>: 제43비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 투계가 표시된 이 마킹은 1970년대 초부터 사용되기 시작했습니다. 이 마킹은 화려한 모습의 수탉이 그려진 비행대의 배지에서 유래한 것으로, 이 비행대의 조종사들은 2차 세계대전 당시에도 수탉을 그려 항공기를 장식했으며, 여러 가지 파생형이 존재했습니다. 이 표식은 제43비행대 소속 맥도넬 더글러스 팬텀에 사용되었으며 수직 안정판에 위치해 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: "Fighting Cock" emblem, No. 43 Squadron, RAF Leuchars, 1978
<Romanian>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn số 43. Hình này hiển thị một con gà đá, và được sử dụng từ đầu những năm 1970. Biểu tượng này được lấy cảm hứng từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn mà cũng miêu tả một con gà trống sặc sỡ; các phi công của sư đoàn này cũng đã sử dụng những con gà này để trang trí máy bay của họ trong Thế chiến thứ hai, với một số biến thể được biết đến. Biểu tượng cụ thể này chỉ được tìm thấy trên các máy bay McDonnell Douglas Phantom được phục vụ trong Sư đoàn số 43, và được đặt trên thân cân bằng dọc.
<HChinese>: 1978 年，盧赫斯，英國皇家空軍第 43 中隊“鬥雞”徽標
<Comments>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.

<English>: A marking of Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. The emblem depicts an outstretched skeletal hand, used on the Ju 88 aircraft of the group. The hand was painted on the side of the nose under the cockpit, as if to grasp the side window.
<French>: Un marquage du Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. L'emblème représente une main squelettique tendue, utilisé sur les avions Ju 88 du groupe. La main était peinte sur le côté sous le cockpit, comme s'elle saisissait le côté de la fenêtre.
<Italian>: Uno stemma del gruppo, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Stormo Bombardieri di Picchiata) 77. Lo stemma ritrae una mano scheletrica, usato sugli aerei Ju 88 operanti nel gruppo. La mano era dipinta sul lato del muso sotto la cabina di pilotaggio, come se volesse agguantare il finestrino.
<German>: Ein Kennzeichen der Stabsgruppe des Sturzkampfgeschwaders 77. Das Abzeichen stellt eine ausgestreckte Skeletthand dar, die auf den Ju 88-Flugzeugen der Gruppe verwendet wurde. Die Hand wurde auf die Seite der Nase unter dem Cockpit gemalt, als ob sie das Seitenfenster greifen wollte.
<Spanish>: Una marca del Grupo de Mando, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Ala de Bombarderos en Inmersión) 77. El emblema representa una mano esquelética extendida, utilizada en los aviones Ju 88 del grupo. La mano estaba pintada en el lateral del morro, bajo la cabina, como si quisiera agarrarse a la ventanilla lateral.
<Polish>: Oznaczenie Grupy Sztabowej, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Skrzydło Bombowców Nurkujących) 77. Emblemat przedstawia wyciągniętą szkieletową dłoń, używany na samolotach Ju 88 grupy. Dłoń była malowana na boku nosa pod kabiną, jakby chwytała boczne okno.
<Czech>: Označení Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. Znak znázorňuje nataženou kostlivou ruku, používanou na letounech Ju 88 této skupiny. Ruka byla namalována na boku přídě pod kokpitem, jako by se chytala bočního okénka.
<Turkish>: A marking of Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. The emblem depicts an outstretched skeletal hand, used on the Ju 88 aircraft of the group. The hand was painted on the side of the nose under the cockpit, as if to grasp the side window.

<French>: Pin-up "Oomph Gal", 408e Escadron de la RCAF
<Chinese>: 加\t拿\t大\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 408 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“热\t情\t姑\t娘”\t涂\t鸦
<Korean>: "Oomph Gal" 핀업, 왕립 캐나다 공군 제 408 비행대
<TChinese>: Hình pin-up 'Oomph Gal', của Sư đoàn số 408 của Không quân Hoàng gia Canada

<English>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<French>: La pin-up " Oomph Gal " du Lancaster KB929 en 1945, 408e escadron de la RCAF. Comme beaucoup de pin-up de l'époque, celle-ci est inspirée d'une actrice populaire de l'époque, Ann Sheridan, que les médias appelaient la "Oomph girl" - bien qu'elle-même ne soit pas tout à fait sûre de la signification du titre de "Oomph girl". La pin-up a été peinte juste sous le côté du cockpit.
<Italian>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Spanish>: Pin-up "Oomph Gal" del Lancaster KB929 durante 1945, Escuadrón No. 408 de la RCAF. Como muchos pin-ups de la época, este ejemplo se basaba en una popular actriz de la época, Ann Sheridan, a la que los medios de comunicación llamaban la "Chica Oomph" - aunque se decía que ella misma no estaba del todo segura de lo que significaba realmente el título de "Chica Oomph". El pin-up se pintó justo debajo del lateral de la cabina.
<Polish>: „Oomph Gal” pin-up Lancastra KB929 w 1945 roku, 408 Dywizjon RCAF. Jak wiele pin-upów z tamtej epoki, ten przykład był oparty na popularnej wówczas aktorce, Ann Sheridan, która była nazywana przez media „Oomph girl” - chociaż sama aktorka nie była całkowicie pewna, co właściwie oznaczał ten tytuł. Pin-up został namalowany tuż pod bokiem kabiny.
<Czech>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Turkish>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Chinese>: 该\t涂\t鸦\t见\t于 1945 年\t间\t隶\t属\t于\t加\t拿\t大\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 408 轰\t炸\t机\t中\t队\t的 1 架\t兰\t开\t斯\t特\t轰\t炸\t机 (编\t号 KB929) 座\t舱\t玻\t璃\t侧\t面。\t同\t一\t时\t期\t的\t机\t鼻\t涂\t鸦\t往\t往\t以\t当\t时\t走\t红\t的\t女\t演\t员\t形\t象\t作\t为\t创\t作\t原\t型，\t这\t一\t图\t案\t也\t来\t自\t大\t众\t媒\t体\t所\t评\t选\t的\t“热\t情\t姑\t娘”\t安·谢\t里\t登；\t尽\t管\t即\t使\t是\t演\t员\t自\t己\t可\t能\t也\t对\t标\t语\t所\t含\t的\t意\t味\t不\t甚\t明\t了。
<Ukrainian>: Пінап «Oomph Gal» на Lancaster KB929 у 1945 році, 408-а ескадрилья RCAF. Як і багато пінапів тієї епохи, цей приклад базувався на популярній на той час актрисі Енн Шерідан, яку в медіа називали «дівчиною Oomph», хоча вона сама не зовсім впевнена, що титул «дівчина Oomph» насправді означав. Пінап був намальований прямо під бортиком кабіни.
<Serbian>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Hungarian>: Oomph Gal pin-up. Kanadai Királyi Légierő 408. százada (1945).
<Korean>: 캐나다 공군의 랭카스터 KB929에 부착된 "움프 걸" 핀업입니다. 다른 핀업들처럼 당대 유명한 여배우였던 앤 셰리든의 모습을 따라 제작되었습니다. 앤 셰리든은 미디어에서 "움프 걸"로 불렸지만, 그녀 자신도 "움프 걸" 이라는 칭호가 실제로는 어떤 의미인지는 잘 알지 못했다고 합니다. 이 핀업은 조종석 측면 바로 아래에 그려져 있었습니다.
<Romanian>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<TChinese>: Bức họa 'Oomph Gal' trên máy bay Lancaster KB929 trong năm 1945, của Sư đoàn số 408 của Không quân Hoàng gia Canada. Giống như nhiều hình pin-up của thời đại đó, ví dụ này được dựa trên một nữ diễn viên nổi tiếng vào thời điểm đó, Ann Sheridan, người được truyền thông gắn với danh hiệu 'Oomph girl' - mặc dù cô ấy chính bản thân cũng không chắc chắn rằng "Oomph girl" có ý nghĩa gì. Bức họa pin-up này được vẽ ngay dưới bên hông buồng lái.
<HChinese>: 1945 年，加拿大皇家空軍，第 408 中隊，“熱情姑娘”塗鴉
<Comments>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.

<English>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’s marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’s roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.
<French>: Le marquage personnel de (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, Escadron No. 603, RAuxAF. Le marquage de David est directement lié à son nom, Scottie étant un surnom affectueux courant de Scott. Il s'agit également du surnom de la race de chien Scottish Terrier, qui apparaît également dans la cocarde de David. Le marquage et l'inscription qui l'accompagne ont été placés sous l'arrière de l'échappement du moteur de son Spitfire en 1941.
<Italian>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’s marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’s roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.
<German>: "Scottie"-Bugbemalung, Flt Lt Francis "Scottie" Scott-Malden, Nr. 603 Squadron, RAF, 1941
<Spanish>: El distintivo personal de (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, Escuadrón No. 603, RAuxAF. El distintivo de David está directamente relacionado con su nombre, ya que Scottie es un apodo cariñoso común de Scott. Por cierto, también es el apodo de la raza de perro Scottish Terrier, que también aparece en la escarapela de David. La marca y la inscripción que la acompaña se colocaron debajo de la parte trasera del tubo de escape del motor de su Spitfire en 1941.
<Russian>: Персональная эмблема "Scottie", пилот Фрэнсис "Скотти" Скотт-Молден, 603-я эскадрилья RAF, 1941
<Polish>: Osobisty emblemat (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, 603 Dywizjon, RAuxAF. Emblemat Davida odnosi się bezpośrednio do jego nazwiska, ponieważ "Scottie" to popularne pieszczotliwe przezwisko od Scott. Przypadkowo jest to również nazwa rasy psa - Scottish Terrier, który pojawia się w emblemacie Davida. Oznaczenie wraz z napisem było umieszczone pod tyłem wylotu silnika na jego Spitfire w 1941 roku.
<Czech>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’s marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’s roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.

<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t辅\t助\t空\t军\t第 603 飞\t行\t中\t队\t佛\t朗\t西\t斯·戴\t维·斯\t蒂\t芬·斯\t科\t特\t-\t马\t尔\t登\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦。\t戴\t维\t的\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦\t与\t他\t的\t姓\t氏\t相\t关：\t“斯\t科\t蒂”\t在\t当\t时\t是\t斯\t科\t特\t的\t常\t见\t亲\t密\t昵\t称，\t而\t这\t一\t称\t呼\t恰\t巧\t也\t是\t苏\t格\t兰\t梗\t犬\t的\t外\t号\t之\t一；\t戴\t维\t的\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦\t乃\t至\t识\t别\t条\t带\t也\t因\t此\t选\t取\t了\t苏\t格\t兰\t梗\t的\t形\t象。\t戴\t维·马\t尔\t登\t喷\t火\t座\t机 1941 年\t时\t在\t引\t擎\t排\t气\t管\t后\t方\t绘\t有\t这\t一\t涂\t鸦\t与\t对\t应\t的\t标\t语。
<Japanese>: "Scottie" nose art, Flt Lt Francis "Scottie" Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAF, 1941
<Portuguese>: Arte do nariz "Scottie", Flt Lt Francis "Scottie" Scott-Malden, Esquadrão No. 603, RAF, 1941
<Ukrainian>: Особисте маркування (Френсіса) Девіда Стівена Скотта-Малдена, 603-а ескадрилья, RAuxAF. Позначка Девіда безпосередньо пов’язана з його ім’ям, а Скотті – це загальне ласкаве прізвисько Скотта. До речі, це також прізвисько собаки породи шотландський тер’єр, який також з’являється в ронделі Девіда. Маркування та супровідний напис були розташовані під задньою частиною вихлопу двигуна на його Spitfire у 1941 році.
