The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.
<TChinese>: Dấu hiệu cá nhân của (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, Phi đoàn số 603, RAuxAF. Dấu hiệu của David liên kết trực tiếp với tên của anh, với Scottie là biệt danh thân mật phổ biến của Scott. Ngẫu nhiên, đây cũng là biệt danh của giống chó Scottish Terrier, loại chó này cũng xuất hiện trong huy hiệu tròn của David. Dấu hiệu và dòng chữ đi kèm được đặt dưới phía sau ống xả động cơ trên chiếc Spitfire của anh vào năm 1941.
<HChinese>: 1941 年，英國皇家空軍第 630 中隊，弗朗西斯·“蘇格蘭梗”·斯科特-莫爾登上尉，“蘇格蘭梗”機鼻塗鴉
<Comments>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’\ts marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’\ts roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.

<English>: An emblem used by Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. The group operated numerous aircraft, with the emblem being specific to the particular aircraft it was placed on. The emblem came in several colorations depending on the group, this blue marking of Fliegende Staffel (Flying Group) 2 was placed on the tail of the F-104 Starfighters they operated.
<French>: Un emblème utilisé par le Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. Le groupe a opéré sur nombreux avions, avec l'emblème étant spécifique à l'avion particulier sur lequel il a été placé. L'emblème est venu dans plusieurs colorations dépendant du groupe, ce marquage bleu du Fliegende Staffel (Flying Group) 2 était placé sur la queue des F-104 Starfighters qu'ils opéraient.
<Italian>: An emblem used by Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. The group operated numerous aircraft, with the emblem being specific to the particular aircraft it was placed on. The emblem came in several colorations depending on the group, this blue marking of Fliegende Staffel (Flying Group) 2 was placed on the tail of the F-104 Starfighters they operated.
<German>: Ein Abzeichen, das vom Jagdbombergeschwader 33 verwendet wurde. Die Gruppe betrieb zahlreiche Flugzeuge, wobei das Abzeichen dem jeweiligen Flugzeug zugeordnet war. Das Abzeichen gab es je nach Gruppe in verschiedenen Farben. Dieses blaue Abzeichen der Fliegenden Staffel 2 befand sich auf dem Heck der von ihr eingesetzten F-104 Starfighter.
<Spanish>: Emblema utilizado por la Jagdbombergeschwader (Ala de Cazabombarderos) 33. El grupo operaba numerosos aviones, y el emblema era específico del avión concreto en el que se colocaba. El emblema tenía varias coloraciones según el grupo, esta marca azul del Fliegende Staffel (Grupo Volante) 2 se colocaba en la cola de los F-104 Starfighters que operaban.
<Polish>: Emblemat używany przez Jagdbombergeschwader 33. Grupa operowała licznymi samolotami, a emblemat był specyficzny dla konkretnego samolotu, na którym był umieszczony. Emblemat występował w kilku kolorach w zależności od grupy, ten niebieski znak Fliegende Staffel 2 był umieszczony na ogonie samolotów F-104 Starfighter, które operowali.
<Czech>: Emblém používaný Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. Skupina provozovala řadu letounů, přičemž znak byl specifický pro konkrétní letoun, na kterém byl umístěn. Emblém existoval v několika barevných provedeních v závislosti na skupině, toto modré označení Fliegende Staffel (Létající skupiny) 2 bylo umístěno na ocase jimi provozovaných stíhaček F-104 Starfighter.

<French>: Emblème de Tête de Renard, Escadron No. 12
<Spanish>: Emblema Cabeza de Zorro, Escuadrón No. 12
<Chinese>: 第 12 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“狐\t狸\t头”\t徽\t标
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng đầu cáo, Phi đoàn số 12

<English>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<French>: Un emblème de l'escadron n° 12. L'emblème représente une tête de renard hargneuse, une reproduction fidèle de l'insigne de l'escadron. La tête de renard a été choisie comme emblème de la 12e escadrille car, en 1926, elle a été la première à être équipée du Fairey Fox, un chasseur puissant pour l'époque et un symbole fort de fierté pour le groupe. Ce marquage plus moderne a cependant été apposé sur plusieurs Buccaneer de la 12e escadrille, sur le côté des entrées d'air des moteurs.
<Italian>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<German>: "Fuchskopf" Abzeichen, Lossiemouth Buccaneer Wing, No. 12 Squadron, RAF
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón No. 12. El emblema representa una cabeza de zorro gruñendo, una reproducción idéntica de la insignia del escuadrón. Se eligió la cabeza de zorro como emblema del No. 12 porque en 1926 fue el primer escuadrón equipado con el Fairey Fox, un poderoso caza para la época y un fuerte símbolo de orgullo para el grupo. Sin embargo, esta marca más moderna se colocó en varios atacantes Buccaneer del No. 12, y se situó en el lateral de las tomas de los motores.
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry nr 12. Emblemat przedstawia głowę warczącego lisa, wierną kopię herbu eskadry. Głowa lisa została wybrana jako emblemat Eskadry nr 12, ponieważ w 1926 roku była to pierwsza eskadra wyposażona w samolot Fairey Fox, potężny myśliwiec tamtych czasów i silny symbol dumy dla grupy. Ten bardziej nowoczesny emblemat został jednak umieszczony na kilku atakujących samolotach Buccaneer Eskadry nr 12 i znajdował się po bokach wlotów silników.
<Czech>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<Turkish>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 12 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t忠\t实\t还\t原\t了\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t中\t咆\t哮\t的\t狐\t狸\t头\t图\t案。\t中\t队\t于 1926 年\t成\t为\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t中\t首\t支\t换\t装\t费\t尔\t雷\t“狐”\t式\t战\t斗\t机\t的\t部\t队；\t为\t了\t彰\t显\t率\t先\t换\t装\t新\t型\t战\t机\t的\t自\t豪\t之\t情，\t中\t队\t决\t定\t将\t狐\t狸\t形\t象\t列\t入\t官\t方\t纹\t章，\t确\t立\t为\t部\t队\t的\t象\t征。\t游\t戏\t中\t的\t这\t枚\t贴\t花\t则\t是\t后\t期\t以\t现\t代\t风\t格\t重\t绘\t的\t版\t本，\t主\t要\t见\t于\t第 12 中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t掠\t夺\t者\t攻\t击\t机，\t喷\t绘\t于\t引\t擎\t进\t气\t道\t两\t侧。
<Japanese>: "Fox Head" emblem, Lossiemouth Buccaneer Wing, No. 12 Squadron, RAF
<Portuguese>: Emblema "Fox Head", Ala Lossiemouth Buccaneer, Esquadrão No. 12, RAF
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 12-ї ескадрильї. На емблемі зображена голова лиса, що гарчить, один в один із виконанням значка ескадрильї. Голову лиса було обрано як емблему для 12-ї, оскільки в 1926 році вони були першою ескадрильєю, яка була оснащена Fairey Fox, потужним винищувачем того часу та сильним символом гордості для групи. Однак це більш сучасне маркування було розміщено на кількох штурмовиках Buccaneer 12-ї і було розташоване збоку від впускних отворів двигуна.
<Serbian>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Légierő Lossiemouth Buccaneer ezrede 12. századának emblémája.
<Korean>: 제12비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 이 엠블럼은 비행대 배지를 표현한 으르렁거리는 모습의 여우가 그려져 있습니다. 여우의 머리는 1926년 당시 강력한 성능의 전투기였던 페어리 폭스를 최초로 운용했던 것에서 비롯된 것으로, 제12비행대의 상징으로도 알려져 있었습니다. 그러나 이보다 현대적인 표식이 제12비행대의 버캐니어에 사용되었으며 엔진 흡기구 측면에 부착되어 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: "Fox Head" emblem, Lossiemouth Buccaneer Wing, No. 12 Squadron, RAF
<Romanian>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Phi đoàn số 12. Biểu tượng mô tả đầu cáo gầm gừ, một phiên bản chính xác một-tỷ-lệ-một của huy hiệu phi đoàn. Đầu cáo được chọn làm biểu tượng cho Phi đoàn số 12 vì vào năm 1926, họ là phi đoàn đầu tiên được trang bị Fairey Fox, một loại máy bay chiến đấu mạnh mẽ cho thời điểm đó và là biểu tượng tự hào mạnh mẽ cho nhóm. Tuy nhiên, dấu hiệu hiện đại hơn này được đặt trên một số máy bay tấn công Buccaneer của Phi đoàn số 12, và được đặt ở bên cạnh lỗ hút khí động cơ.
<HChinese>: 英國洛西茅斯，英國皇家空軍第 12 中隊所屬“掠奪者”攻擊機，“狐狸頭”機翼徽標

<Chinese>: 第 237 作\t战\t转\t训\t中\t队\t徽\t标

<HChinese>: 第 237 作戰轉換中隊徽標

<English>: The emblem of No. 237 Operational Conversion Unit. No. 237 operated as a training unit, with the longest run of activity being from March 1971 to October 1991, where they flew Blackburn Buccaneers and several Hawker Hunter variants in training roles. The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<French>: L'emblème de l'unité de conversion opérationnelle n° 237. Le No. 237 a opéré en tant qu'unité d'entraînement, avec la plus longue période d'activité de mars 1971 à octobre 1991, où ils ont piloté des Blackburn Buccaneer et plusieurs variantes de Hawker Hunter dans des rôles d'entraînement. L'emblème représente une paire de sabres croisés derrière un chapeau académique. L'emblème était placé sur le côté des entrées d'air des Buccaneer du groupe, ainsi que sur le côté du nez de plusieurs Hawker Hunter.
<Italian>: The emblem of No. 237 Operational Conversion Unit. No. 237 operated as a training unit, with the longest run of activity being from March 1971 to October 1991, where they flew Blackburn Buccaneers and several Hawker Hunter variants in training roles. The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<Spanish>: Emblema de la Unidad de Conversión Operativa No. 237. El No. 237 funcionó como unidad de entrenamiento, siendo su período de actividad más largo el comprendido entre Marzo de 1971 y Octubre de 1991, en el que volaron Blackburn Buccaneers y varias variantes de Hawker Hunter en funciones de entrenamiento. El emblema muestra un par de sables cruzados detrás de una gorra académica. La marca se colocó en el lateral de las tomas de los motores de los Buccaneers del grupo, y también en el lateral del morro de varios Hawker Hunter.
<Polish>: Emblemat Jednostki Operacyjnego Przekształcenia nr 237. Eskadra nr 237 działała jako jednostka szkoleniowa, z najdłuższym okresem aktywności od marca 1971 do października 1991 roku, podczas którego latała na samolotach Blackburn Buccaneer i kilku wariantach Hawker Hunter w rolach szkoleniowych. Emblemat przedstawia parę skrzyżowanych szabli za akademicką czapką. Znak ten był umieszczony na bokach wlotów silników Buccaneerów tej grupy, a także na bokach nosa kilku samolotów Hawker Hunter.

The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.

The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 237 作\t战\t转\t训\t中\t队 (OCU) 徽\t标。\t作\t战\t转\t训\t中\t队\t承\t担\t机\t型\t转\t换\t的\t训\t练\t任\t务，\t第 237 中\t队\t时\t间\t最\t长\t的\t任\t务\t周\t期\t从 1971 年 3 月\t持\t续\t至 1991 年 10 月，\t期\t间\t主\t要\t使\t用\t布\t莱\t克\t本\t“掠\t夺\t者”\t与\t数\t架\t霍\t克\t“猎\t人”\t系\t列\t战\t机\t进\t行\t训\t练。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t图\t案\t为\t学\t士\t帽\t与\t后\t方\t交\t叉\t弯\t刀\t的\t组\t合，\t主\t要\t喷\t绘\t在\t中\t队\t下\t属\t“掠\t夺\t者”\t攻\t击\t机\t发\t动\t机\t进\t气\t道\t两\t侧\t与\t霍\t克\t“猎\t人”\t机\t鼻\t侧\t面\t位\t置。
<Japanese>: Emblem of the 237th OCU Squadron, RAF
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 237-ї ОКП. 237-а працювала як тренувальна одиниця, причому найдовша діяльність тривала з березня 1971 року по жовтень 1991 року, де вони літали на літаках Blackburn Buccaneer і кількох варіантах Hawker Hunter на тренувальних ролях. На емблемі зображено пару схрещених сабель за академічною шапкою. Маркування було розташоване збоку від впускних отворів двигуна на Buccaneer групи, а також збоку від носа на кількох Hawker Hunter.

<Korean>: 제237전환훈련대에서 사용한 엠블럼입니다. 제237전환훈련대는 1971년 3월부터 1991년 10월까지 장기간 운용되었는데, 블랙번 버캐니어와 수 대의 호커 헌터를 훈련기로 활용한 이력이 있었습니다. 해당 엠블럼은 학사모 뒤에 한 쌍의 검이 교차된 모습을 하고 있습니다. 이 엠블럼은 블랙번 버캐니어의 엔진 흡입구 측면과 일부 호커 헌터의 기수 측면에 배치되어 있었습니다.

<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Đơn vị Chuyển đổi Chiến dịch số 237. Đơn vị số 237 hoạt động như một đơn vị đào tạo, với thời gian hoạt động dài nhất từ tháng 3 năm 1971 đến tháng 10 năm 1991, nơi họ bay Blackburn Buccaneers và một số biến thể của Hawker Hunter trong các vai trò đào tạo. Biểu tượng thể hiện một cặp kiếm cutlass chéo nhau phía sau một mũ học vị. Dấu hiệu này được đặt ở bên cạnh lỗ hút khí động cơ trên các máy bay Buccaneers của nhóm, và cũng ở bên cạnh mũi trên một số Hawker Hunters.

<English>: The emblem of Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. The unit was formed in 1959 and was initially equipped with CL-13 jet fighters, but since went on to operate a variety of aircraft including the F-4 Phantom II and MiG-29. The emblem was most commonly positioned on the tail, but aircraft such as the F-4 had it placed on the side of the fuselage behind the cockpit.
<French>: L'emblème du Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. L'unité a été formée en 1956 et était initialement équipé avec des chasseurs à réactions CL-13, mais depuis elle a continué à opérer sur divers avions incluant le F-4 Phantom II et le MiG-29. L'emblème était le plus souvent positionné sur la queue, mais un avion tel que le F-4 l'avait sur le côté du fuselage derrière le cockpit.
<Italian>: The emblem of Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. The unit was formed in 1959 and was initially equipped with CL-13 jet fighters, but since went on to operate a variety of aircraft including the F-4 Phantom II and MiG-29. The emblem was most commonly positioned on the tail, but aircraft such as the F-4 had it placed on the side of the fuselage behind the cockpit.
<German>: Das Abzeichen des Jagdgeschwaders 73. Die Einheit wurde 1959 gegründet und war zunächst mit CL-13-Düsenjägern ausgerüstet, setzte aber später eine Vielzahl von Flugzeugen ein, darunter die F-4 Phantom II und die MiG-29. Das Abzeichen befand sich in der Regel auf dem Leitwerk, bei Flugzeugen wie der F-4 war es jedoch auch seitlich am Rumpf hinter dem Cockpit angebracht.
<Spanish>: Emblema de la Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 73. La unidad se formó en 1959 y al principio estaba equipada con cazas a reacción CL-13, pero desde entonces pasó a operar una variedad de aviones, incluidos el F-4 Phantom II y el MiG-29. El emblema se colocaba normalmente en la cola, pero en aviones como el F-4 se colocaba en el lateral del fuselaje, detrás de la cabina.
<Polish>: Emblemat Jagdgeschwader 73. Jednostka została utworzona w 1959 roku i początkowo była wyposażona w myśliwce CL-13, ale później operowała różnymi samolotami, w tym F-4 Phantom II i MiG-29. Emblemat był najczęściej umieszczany na ogonie, ale samoloty takie jak F-4 miały go umieszczony na boku kadłuba za kabiną.
<Czech>: Znak Jagdgeschwader (Stíhacího křídla) 73. Jednotka byla zformována v roce 1959 a zpočátku byla vybavena proudovými stíhačkami CL-13, ale od té doby provozovala celou řadu letounů včetně F-4 Phantom II a MiG-29. Znak byl nejčastěji umístěn na ocase, ale letouny jako F-4 jej měly umístěn na boku trupu za pilotní kabinou.
<Turkish>: The emblem of Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. The emblem was most commonly positioned on the tail, but aircraft such as the F-4 had it placed on the side of the fuselage behind the cockpit.

<French>: Emblème des "Pirates du ciel", escadron n° 208
<Chinese>: 第 208 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“空\t中\t海\t盗”\t徽\t标
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng "Hải tặc bầu trời", Phi đoàn số 208

<English>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<French>: L'emblème des "Pirates du ciel", escadron n° 208. Les Buccaneers de cet escadron portaient tous une variante du drapeau pirate Jolly Roger ainsi que l'inscription "Sky Pirates" - chaque crâne variait, certains arborant une expression colérique tandis que d'autres étaient plus joviaux, cette version manque de quelques dents et semble également porter un casque d'écoute. Tous les marquages ont été placés au même endroit, juste sous l'avant du cockpit sur le côté gauche.
<Italian>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Spanish>: El emblema de los "Piratas del Cielo", Escuadrón No. 208. Todos los Buccaneers de este escuadrón llevaban alguna variante de la bandera pirata del jolly roger junto con la inscripción "Piratas del Cielo" - cada calavera variaba, algunas lucían expresiones de enfado mientras que otras eran más joviales, a esta versión le faltan algunos dientes y también parece llevar auriculares. Todas las marcas estaban colocadas en el mismo lugar, justo debajo de la parte delantera de la cabina, a babor.
<Polish>: Emblemat „Sky Pirates” 208 Dywizjonu. Buccaneery tego dywizjonu miały różne wersje flagi pirackiej "jolly roger" wraz z napisem "Sky Pirates" - każda czaszka była inna, niektóre miały gniewne wyrazy, inne były bardziej wesołe. Ten konkretny emblemat ma brakujące zęby i wydaje się nosić słuchawki. Wszystkie oznaczenia były umieszczone w tym samym miejscu, tuż pod przodem kabiny po lewej stronie.
<Czech>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Turkish>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Chinese>: 皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 208 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“空\t中\t海\t盗”\t徽\t标。\t该\t中\t队\t下\t属\t掠\t夺\t者\t攻\t击\t机\t最\t引\t人\t瞩\t目\t的\t外\t观\t特\t征\t莫\t过\t于\t机\t身\t喷\t绘\t有\t各\t种\t样\t式\t的\t海\t盗\t旗\t以\t及\t“空\t中\t海\t盗”\t标\t语。\t海\t盗\t旗\t上\t的\t骷\t髅\t神\t态\t各\t异，\t有\t的\t面\t露\t愠\t色，\t有\t的\t神\t情\t欢\t快，\t游\t戏\t中\t的\t这\t枚\t徽\t标\t则\t少\t了\t几\t颗\t牙\t齿，\t似\t乎\t还\t戴\t着\t飞\t行\t耳\t机。\t所\t有\t海\t盗\t旗\t徽\t标\t均\t喷\t绘\t于\t座\t舱\t前\t方\t的\t左\t侧\t机\t身\t蒙\t皮\t位\t置。
<Ukrainian>: Емблема «Небесні пірати», 208-а ескадрилья. Усі пірати цієї ескадрильї носили певний варіант піратського прапора Веселого Роджера разом із написом «Небесні пірати» — кожен череп був різним, деякі мали гнівний вираз обличчя, а інші були більш веселими, у цій версії бракує кількох зубів, а також, як видно він в навушниках. Усі позначки були розташовані в одному місці, прямо під передньою частиною кабіни з лівого борту.
<Serbian>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Hungarian>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Korean>: 제208비행대가 사용한 "Sky Pirates" 엠블럼입니다. 이 비행대에서 버캐니어를 조종했던 조종사들은, “Sky Priates(하늘의 해적)” 이라는 해적 깃발이 그려진 데칼을 사용했는데, 각 해골의 모습 또한 다양했다고 합니다. 본 데칼은 화난 표정을 가지고 있지만 다른 표정들의 경우 더 유쾌한 모습을 가지고 있었습니다. 이 버전은 몇 개의 치아가 빠진 상태로 헤드폰을 착용한 모습을 하고 있습니다. 이러한 데칼은 모두 조종석 좌측 아래 동체에 위치해 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Romanian>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng "Hải tặc bầu trời" của Phi đoàn số 208. Những chiếc Buccaneers của phi đoàn này đều mang một phiên bản nào đó của lá cờ cướp biển jolly roger cùng với dòng chữ "Sky Pirates" - mỗi bộ hài cốt đều khác nhau, một số mang vẻ mặt tức giận trong khi những cái khác lại vui vẻ hơn, phiên bản này thiếu vài chiếc răng và cũng dường như đang đeo tai nghe. Tất cả các dấu hiệu đều được đặt ở cùng một vị trí, ngay dưới phía trước của buồng lái ở phía bên trái.

<TChinese>: Huy hiệu của Phi đoàn số 450, RAAF

<English>: The badge of No. 450 Squadron, RAAF. The squadron was formed on the 16th of February 1941 and flew Tomahawks and Kittyhawks over the middle east in various combat roles. The badge displays the head of a Jaguar pierced by a rapier, along with the squadron motto "Harass". This motto earned No. 450 squadron the unofficial nickname of "The Desert Harassers" after their prolific ground attack operations.
<French>: L'insigne de l'escadron 450 de la RAAF. L'escadron a été formé le 16 février 1941 et a piloté des Tomahawks et des Kittyhawks au-dessus du Moyen-Orient dans divers rôles de combat. L'insigne représente la tête d'un Jaguar transpercée par une rapière, ainsi que la devise de l'escadron, "Harass". Cette devise a valu à l'escadron n° 450 le surnom officieux de " Desert Harassers " (les harceleurs du désert) en raison de ses prolifiques opérations d'attaque au sol.
<Italian>: The badge of No. 450 Squadron, RAAF. The squadron was formed on the 16th of February 1941 and flew Tomahawks and Kittyhawks over the middle east in various combat roles. The badge displays the head of a Jaguar pierced by a rapier, along with the squadron motto "Harass". This motto earned No. 450 squadron the unofficial nickname of "The Desert Harassers" after their prolific ground attack operations.
<Spanish>: Insignia del Escuadrón No. 450 de la RAAF. El escuadrón se formó el 16 de Febrero de 1941 y voló Tomahawks y Kittyhawks sobre Oriente Medio en diversas funciones de combate. La insignia muestra la cabeza de un Jaguar atravesada por un estoque, junto con el lema del escuadrón "Hostigar". Este lema le valió al escuadrón No. 450 el apodo no oficial de "Los Hostigadores del Desierto" por sus prolíficas operaciones de ataque a tierra.
<Polish>: Odznaka 450 Dywizjonu, RAAF. Dywizjon został utworzony 16 lutego 1941 roku i latał na Tomahawkach i Kittyhawkach nad Bliskim Wschodem w różnych rolach bojowych. Odznaka przedstawia głowę jaguara przebitą rapierem, wraz z mottem dywizjonu "Harass". To motto nadało 450 Dywizjonowi nieoficjalny przydomek "The Desert Harassers" po ich licznych operacjach ataków naziemnych.
<Czech>: The badge of No. 450 Squadron, RAAF. The squadron was formed on the 16th of February 1941 and flew Tomahawks and Kittyhawks over the middle east in various combat roles. This motto earned No. 450 squadron the unofficial nickname of "The Desert Harassers" after their prolific ground attack operations.

<Chinese>: 澳\t大\t利\t亚\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 450 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t部\t队\t组\t建\t于 1941 年 2 月 16 日，\t早\t期\t主\t要\t装\t备\t“战\t斧”\t和\t“小\t鹰”\t战\t斗\t机\t在\t中\t东\t战\t区\t执\t行\t作\t战\t任\t务。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t为\t长\t剑\t刺\t穿\t美\t洲\t豹\t头\t颅\t的\t图\t案，\t下\t方\t列\t有\t中\t队\t格\t言\t“侵\t扰\t袭\t击” - 这\t一\t格\t言\t源\t自 450 中\t队\t在\t执\t行\t对\t地\t攻\t击\t任\t务\t中\t斩\t获\t大\t量\t战\t果\t而\t获\t得\t的\t非\t正\t式\t外\t号\t“沙\t漠\t袭\t扰\t者”。
<Japanese>: オーストラリア\t空軍第\t450飛行中隊の\t記章
<Ukrainian>: Знак 450-ї ескадрильї RAAF. Ескадрилья була сформована 16-го лютого 1941 року і здійснювала польоти на «Томагавках» і «Кіттігавках» над Близьким Сходом у різних бойових завданнях. На значку зображена голова ягуара, пронизана рапірою, разом із девізом ескадрильї «Harass». За цим девізом 450-а ескадрилья отримала неофіційне прізвисько «Гнітники пустелі» після плідних наземних атакувальних операцій.

<Korean>: 영국 공군 제450비행대의 배지입니다. 이 비행대는 1941년 2월 16일에 창설되어 토마호크와 키티호크를 운용하였습니다. 이 배지에는 재규어의 머리가 레이피어에 의해 관통되어 있는 모습과 함께 비행대의 모토인 "Harass" 가 쓰여 있습니다. 이 모토 때문에, 제450비행대는 성공적인 지상 공격 임무를 수행할 때 마다 "The Desert Harassers" 라는 비공식 별명으로 불렸다고 합니다

<TChinese>: Huy hiệu của Phi đoàn số 450, RAAF. Phi đoàn được thành lập vào ngày 16 tháng 2 năm 1941 và đã bay Tomahawks và Kittyhawks trên Trung Đông trong các vai trò chiến đấu khác nhau. Huy hiệu thể hiện đầu của một con Báo đốm bị một thanh kiếm Rapier đâm xuyên, cùng với phương châm của phi đoàn là "Harass" (Quấy rối). Phương châm này đã giúp Phi đoàn số 450 có biệt danh không chính thức là "Những Kẻ Quấy rối Sa mạc" sau những chiến dịch tấn công mặt đất hiệu quả của họ.

<Chinese>: 第 2\t“殷\t麦\t曼”\t俯\t冲\t轰\t炸\t机\t联\t队\t徽\t标
<HChinese>: 第 2“殷麥曼”俯衝轟炸機聯隊徽標

<English>: The main emblem of Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 2, a black cross on a white crusader shield. Being the emblem of the entire Wing, this marking was very rarely used on aircraft, with only the standard group insignia being used in the majority of examples. However several early Ju 87 models did wear the marking under the front of the cockpit.
<French>: Le principal emblème du Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 2, une croix noire sur un bouclier de croisé blanc. Étant l'emblème de la Wing entière, ce marquage était très rarement utilisé sur des avions, avec seulement l'insigne standard du groupe utilisé dans la majorité des exemples. Cependant plusieurs premiers modèle de Ju 87 portait ce marquage sous l'avant du cockpit.
<Italian>: The main emblem of Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 2, a black cross on a white crusader shield. Being the emblem of the entire Wing, this marking was very rarely used on aircraft, with only the standard group insignia being used in the majority of examples. However several early Ju 87 models did wear the marking under the front of the cockpit.
<German>: Das Hauptabzeichen des Sturzkampfgeschwaders 2, ein schwarzes Kreuz auf einem weißen Kreuzritterschild. Da es sich um das Emblem des gesamten Geschwaders handelt, wurde dieses Abzeichen nur sehr selten auf den Flugzeugen verwendet; die meisten Exemplare trugen nur das Standardgruppenabzeichen. Einige frühe Ju 87-Modelle trugen die Kennzeichnung jedoch unter der Vorderseite des Cockpits.
<Spanish>: El emblema principal de la Sturzkampfgeschwader (Ala de Bombarderos en Inmersión) 2, una cruz negra sobre un escudo cruzado blanco. Al ser el emblema de toda el Ala, esta marca se utilizaba muy raramente en los aviones, y en la mayoría de los ejemplos sólo se utilizaba la insignia estándar del grupo. Sin embargo, algunos de los primeros modelos de Ju 87 llevaban la marca bajo la parte delantera de la cabina.
<Russian>: Эмблема эскадры непосредственной поддержки войск StG 2 "Иммельман" Люфтваффе
<Polish>: Główny emblemat Sturzkampfgeschwader 2. Czarny krzyż na białej tarczy krzyżowca był rzadko używany na samolotach, będąc emblematem całej grupy, z wyjątkiem standardowych insygniów grupy używanych w większości przykładów. Jednakże kilka wczesnych modeli Ju 87 nosiło oznaczenie pod przodem kabiny.
<Czech>: Hlavní znak Sturzkampfgeschwader (střemhlavé bombardovací křídlo) 2, černý kříž na bílém křižáckém štítu. Vzhledem k tomu, že se jednalo o znak celého křídla, bylo toto označení na letounech používáno velmi zřídka, na většině exemplářů byl použit pouze standardní znak skupiny. Nicméně několik raných modelů Ju 87 neslo toto označení pod přední částí kokpitu.
<Turkish>: The main emblem of Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 2, a black cross on a white crusader shield. However several early Ju 87 models did wear the marking under the front of the cockpit.

<HChinese>: 第 2 俯衝轟炸機聯隊徽標，圖案為飾有黑色十字的白色十字軍盾牌。儘管該標識為第 2 俯衝轟炸機聯隊的官方徽標，部隊所屬戰機卻甚少將其塗佈在機身上，大多數戰機僅塗有所屬中隊的標識。不過數架早期型 Ju 87 轟炸機的確在座艙下的機身部位繪有這一徽標。

Being the emblem of the entire Wing, this marking was very rarely used on aircraft, with only the standard group insignia being used in the majority of examples. However several early Ju 87 models did wear the marking under the front of the cockpit.

<English>: The badge of No. 27 Squadron, RAF. The squadron formed on the 5th of November 1915, and has been disbanded and reformed numerous times throughout its lifetime. It operated in the First World War as well as the Second, and currently flies Chinook helicopters. The emblem derives from the squadron’s early connection with India where it operated, and also that the first aircraft used by the squadron were Martinsyde G.100 Elephants. The squadron’s motto, "Quam celerrime ad astra", translates to "With all speed to the Stars".
<French>: L'insigne de l'escadron n° 27 de la RAF. L'escadron a été formé le 5 novembre 1915 et a été dissous et reformé à de nombreuses reprises au cours de son existence. Il a participé à la Première Guerre mondiale ainsi qu'à la Seconde, et vole actuellement sur des hélicoptères Chinook. L'emblème de l'escadron provient de ses premiers liens avec l'Inde, où il a opéré, et du fait que les premiers avions utilisés par l'escadron étaient des Martinsyde G.100 Elephants. La devise de l'escadron, "Quam celerrime ad astra", se traduit par "À toute vitesse vers les étoiles".
<Italian>: The badge of No. 27 Squadron, RAF. The squadron formed on the 5th of November 1915, and has been disbanded and reformed numerous times throughout its lifetime. It operated in the First World War as well as the Second, and currently flies Chinook helicopters. The emblem derives from the squadron’s early connection with India where it operated, and also that the first aircraft used by the squadron were Martinsyde G.100 Elephants. The squadron’s motto, "Quam celerrime ad astra", translates to "With all speed to the Stars".
<Spanish>: Insignia del Escuadrón No. 27 de la RAF. El escuadrón se formó el 5 de Noviembre de 1915, y ha sido disuelto y reformado numerosas veces a lo largo de su vida. Operó tanto en la Primera Guerra Mundial como en la Segunda, y actualmente vuela helicópteros Chinook. El emblema deriva de la temprana conexión del escuadrón con la India, donde operó, y también de que los primeros aviones utilizados por el escuadrón fueron Martinsyde G.100 Elephants. El lema del escuadrón, "Quam celerrime ad astra", se traduce como "A toda velocidad hacia las estrellas".
<Polish>: Odznaka Eskadry nr 27 RAF. Eskadra została sformowana 5 listopada 1915 roku i wielokrotnie była rozwiązana i ponownie formowana w ciągu swojego istnienia. Działała zarówno w czasie Pierwszej Wojny Światowej, jak i Drugiej, a obecnie lata na śmigłowcach Chinook. Emblemat pochodzi z wczesnego związku eskadry z Indiami, gdzie operowała, oraz od pierwszych samolotów używanych przez eskadrę, Martinsyde G.100 Elephants. Motto eskadry, "Quam celerrime ad astra", tłumaczy się jako "Z całym pędem do gwiazd".

<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 27 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t该\t部\t组\t建\t于 1915 年 11 月，\t成\t立\t后\t历\t经\t多\t次\t解\t散\t重\t组，\t见\t证\t了\t两\t次\t世\t界\t大\t战\t以\t及\t随\t后\t的\t多\t场\t地\t区\t冲\t突，\t如\t今\t主\t要\t装\t备\t美\t制\t“支\t奴\t干”\t直\t升\t机。\t徽\t标\t中\t的\t图\t案\t灵\t感\t源\t于\t部\t队\t早\t期\t在\t英\t属\t印\t度\t驻\t扎，\t以\t及\t首\t款\t装\t备\t为\t马\t丁\t西\t德 G.100\t“象”\t式\t侦\t察\t机\t的\t经\t历。\t中\t队\t格\t言\t为\t“Quam celerrime ad astra”，\t意\t为\t“全\t速\t奔\t赴，\t以\t达\t天\t际”。
<Japanese>: イギリス\t空軍第\t27飛行隊記章
<Ukrainian>: Знак 27-ї ескадрильї RAF. Ескадрилья була сформована 5-го листопада 1915 року і була розформована та реформована багато разів протягом свого існування. Вона діяла під час Першої світової війни, а також Другої, і зараз літає на вертольотах Chinook. Емблема походить від раннього зв’язку ескадрильї з Індією, де вона діяла, а також від того, що першими літаками, які використовувала ескадрилья, були Martinsyde G.100 Elephant. Девіз ескадрильї «Quam celerrime ad astra» перекладається як «З усією швидкістю до зірок».

<Korean>: 영국 공군 제27비행대의 배지입니다. 1915년 11월 5일에 창설된 이 비행대는 일생 동안 수 차례 해체되고 재창설되었습니다. 이 비행대는 제2차 세계 대전뿐만 아니라 제1차 세계 대전에서도 활약하였으며 현재는 치누크 헬리콥터를 운항하고 있습니다. 이 엠블럼은 비행대가 초기에 작전을 수행했던 인도에서 비롯되었으며, 비행대가 사용한 첫 번째 항공기는 마틴시드 G.100 엘리펀트였습니다. 비행단의 모토인 "Quam celerrime adastra" 로, 번역하면 "전속력으로 별을 향해"라고 합니다.

<TChinese>: Huy hiệu của Phi đoàn số 27, RAF. Phi đoàn được thành lập vào ngày 5 tháng 11 năm 1915, và đã được giải thể và tái thành lập nhiều lần trong suốt thời gian tồn tại của mình. Phi đoàn đã hoạt động trong Chiến tranh thế giới thứ nhất cũng như thứ hai, và hiện tại đang bay trực thăng Chinook. Biểu tượng được bắt nguồn từ mối liên hệ sớm của phi đoàn với Ấn Độ nơi nó hoạt động, cũng như việc máy bay đầu tiên mà phi đoàn sử dụng là Martinsyde G.100 Elephants. Phương châm của phi đoàn, "Quam celerrime ad astra", được dịch là "Với tất cả tốc độ đến với các vì sao".

<English>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<French>: L'emblème de l'escadron 111. L'emblème représente deux épées croisées derrière une croix potencée (une croix dont les bras se terminent en forme de " T ") ornée de trois épées arabes. La formation de l'escadron en Palestine en 1917 a probablement inspiré l'inclusion de ces motifs culturels spécifiques dans l'emblème.  Cette variante spécifique du marquage a été apposée sur la dérive du Tornado F.3 ZH554 alors qu'il était en service au sein de l'escadron 111.
<Italian>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<Spanish>: El emblema del Escuadrón No. 111. El emblema muestra dos espadas cruzadas detrás de una cruz potente (una cruz con brazos terminados en forma de "T") adornada con tres espadas Árabes. La formación del escuadrón en Palestina en 1917 probablemente inspiró la inclusión de estos motivos culturales específicos en el emblema.  Esta variación específica de la marca se colocó en el estabilizador vertical del Tornado F.3 ZH554 mientras estuvo en servicio con el No. 111.
<Polish>: Emblemat 111 Eskadry. Przedstawia krzyż laskowany (z ramionami zakończonymi na kształt litery T) na tle dwóch skrzyżowanych mieczy oraz dwa miecze arabskie. Inspiracją dla zawarcia tych motywów był prawdopodobnie fakt uformowania tej jednostki w Palestynie w roku 1917. Niniejszy wariant umieszczono na stateczniku pionowym Tornado F.3 ZH554 w czasie służby tej maszyny w 111 Eskadrze.
<Czech>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<Turkish>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 111 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t为\t后\t方\t衬\t有\t交\t叉\t长\t剑\t的\t横\t杠\t十\t字 (末\t端\t为 T 型\t的\t十\t字\t架) 图\t案，\t十\t字\t中\t央\t饰\t有\t三\t柄\t阿\t拉\t伯\t弯\t刀 - 这\t一\t元\t素\t可\t能\t源\t自\t中\t队\t于 1917 年\t在\t巴\t勒\t斯\t坦\t成\t军\t的\t历\t史。\t游\t戏\t中\t这\t款\t徽\t标\t见\t于\t中\t队\t所\t属\t的\t狂\t风 F.3 型\t战\t机 (编\t号 ZH554)，\t喷\t绘\t于\t垂\t尾\t部\t位。
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 111-ї ескадрильї. На маркуванні зображено два схрещених мечі позаду хреста-потента (хрест із рукавами, що закінчуються літерою «Т»), прикрашеного трьома арабськими мечами. Формування ескадрильї в Палестині в 1917 році, ймовірно, надихнуло включення цих специфічних культурних мотивів в емблему. Цей особливий варіант маркування був розташований на вертикальному стабілізаторі Tornado F.3 ZH554 під час експлуатації у 111-ій.
<Serbian>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<Hungarian>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<Korean>: 제111비행대의 엠블럼입니다.이 마크는 세 개의 아랍 검으로 장식된 크로스 포텐셜 (끝부분이 "T"자 모양인 십자가) 뒤에 두 자루의 검이 교차된 모습을 가지고 있습니다. 1917년 팔레스타인에서 편성된 이 비행대는 엠블럼에 이러한 특정한 문화적 요소를 포함하도록 영감을 한 것으로 보입니다. 이 마크의 파생형 중 하나는 111비행대가 운용하던 토네이도 F.3 ZH554 의 수직안정판 위에 적용되어 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<Romanian>: The emblem of No. 111 Squadron. The marking displays two crossed swords behind a cross potent (a cross with arms ending in "T" shapes) adorned with three Arabic swords. The squadron's formation in Palestine in 1917 likely inspired the inclusion of these specific cultural motifs within the emblem.  This specific variation of the marking was positioned on the vertical stabilizer of Tornado F.3 ZH554 while in service with No. 111.
<TChinese>: Biểu tượng của Phi đoàn số 111. Dấu hiệu thể hiện hai thanh kiếm chéo nhau đằng sau một cây thập tự cường tráng (một loại thập tự với các cánh tay kết thúc bằng hình dạng "T") được trang trí bởi ba thanh kiếm Ả Rập. Việc hình thành phi đoàn tại Palestine vào năm 1917 có lẽ đã truyền cảm hứng cho việc bao gồm những biểu tượng văn hóa cụ thể này trong biểu tượng. Biến thể cụ thể này của dấu hiệu được đặt trên bộ ổn định dọc của Tornado F.3 ZH554 trong khi phục vụ tại Phi đoàn số 111.

<Chinese>: 第 196 舰\t载\t机\t联\t队\t第 3 中\t队\t徽\t标
<HChinese>: 第 196 艦載機聯隊第 3 中隊徽標

<English>: Emblem of 3rd Group, Bordfliegergruppe (Shipboard Group) 196. The aircraft of the unit were intended for use as catapult aircraft on warships, and carried the emblem of a seahorse on a blue shield. The emblem was placed just before the engine cowling on the Ar 196 seaplanes in operation with the group.
<French>: Emblème du 3e groupe, Bordfliegergruppe (groupe embarqué) 196. L'avion de l'unité était en effet utilisé comme avion catapulté sur des navires de guerre, et portait l'emblème d'un hippocampe sur un bouclier bleu. L'emblème était placé juste devant le capot moteur d'hydravion Ar 196 en opération avec le groupe.
<Italian>: Stemma del 3° Gruppo, Bordfliegergruppe (Gruppo Imbarcato) 196. Gli aerei dell'unità erano intesi per essere usati come aerei catapultabili sulle navi da guerra ed avevano lo stemma di un cavalluccio marino su scudo blu. Lo stemma era posto appena prima della cappottatura motore degli idrovolanti Ar 196 operanti nel gruppo.
<German>: Abzeichen der 3. Staffel, Bordfliegergruppe 196. Die Flugzeuge der Einheit waren für den Einsatz als Katapultflugzeuge auf Kriegsschiffen gedacht, und hatten als Abzeichen ein Seepferd auf einem blauen Schild. Das Abzeichen wurde knapp vor der Motorabdeckung der Ar 196 Seeflugzeugen, die von dieser Gruppe operiert wurden, aufgebracht.
<Spanish>: Emblema del 3º Grupo, Bordfliegergruppe (Grupo de a Bordo) 196. Los aviones de la unidad estaban destinados a ser utilizados como aviones catapulta en buques de guerra, y llevaban el emblema de un caballito de mar sobre un escudo azul. El emblema estaba colocado justo antes del capó del motor en los hidroaviones Ar 196 en servicio con el grupo.
<Polish>: Emblemat 3. Grupy, Bordfliegergruppe (Grupa Pokładowa) 196. Samoloty jednostki były przeznaczone do użycia jako katapultowane samoloty na okrętach wojennych i nosiły emblemat konika morskiego na niebieskiej tarczy. Emblemat był umieszczony tuż przed osłoną silnika na wodnosamolotach Ar 196 używanych przez grupę.
<Czech>: Emblém 3. skupiny, Bordfliegergruppe (Lodní skupina) 196. Letouny této jednotky byly určeny k použití jako katapultovací letouny na válečných lodích a nesly znak mořského koníka na modrém štítu. Znak byl umístěn těsně před krytem motoru na hydroplánech Ar 196 provozovaných u této skupiny.
<Turkish>: Emblem of 3rd Group, Bordfliegergruppe (Shipboard Group) 196. The aircraft of the unit were intended for use as catapult aircraft on warships, and carried the emblem of a seahorse on a blue shield. The emblem was placed just before the engine cowling on the Ar 196 seaplanes in operation with the group.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 196 舰\t载\t机\t联\t队\t第 3 中\t队\t徽\t标。\t该\t联\t队\t所\t属\t战\t机\t主\t要\t为\t海\t军\t舰\t艇\t搭\t载\t的\t水\t上\t侦\t察\t机，\t部\t队\t徽\t标\t为\t蓝\t色\t盾\t徽\t背\t景\t上\t的\t海\t马\t图\t案。\t该\t标\t识\t通\t常\t见\t于\t部\t队\t下\t辖 Ar 196 水\t上\t飞\t机\t的\t引\t擎\t整\t流\t罩\t部\t位。

<Chinese>: 第 63 飞\t行\t中\t队\t识\t别\t徽\t标
<TChinese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Phi đoàn số 63
<HChinese>: 英國皇家空軍第 63 中隊識別標誌

<English>: The roundel of No. 63 Squadron. This roundel like most examples incorporates the focal point of the squadron badge into the marking, which displays an arm grasping a battleaxe, accompanied by the striking yellow and black checkerboard. The roundel was positioned along the nose of the Hawker Hunters in service with No. 63, with the head of the axe angled away from the front of the aircraft.
<French>: La cocarde de l'Escadron n° 63. Cette cocarde, comme la plupart des exemplaires, intègre le point central de l'insigne de l'escadron dans le marquage, qui représente un bras saisissant une hache de guerre, accompagné d'un damier jaune et noir. La cocarde était placée le long du nez des Hawker Hunter en service au sein du 63e Escadron, la tête de la hache étant inclinée vers l'avant de l'appareil.
<Italian>: The roundel of No. 63 Squadron. This roundel like most examples incorporates the focal point of the squadron badge into the marking, which displays an arm grasping a battleaxe, accompanied by the striking yellow and black checkerboard. The roundel was positioned along the nose of the Hawker Hunters in service with No. 63, with the head of the axe angled away from the front of the aircraft.
<Spanish>: Escarapela del Escuadrón No. 63. Este escarapela, como la mayoría de los ejemplos, incorpora el punto focal de la insignia del escuadrón en la marca, que muestra un brazo empuñando un hacha de guerra, acompañado por el llamativo damero amarillo y negro. La escarapela se colocaba a lo largo del morro de los Hawker Hunter en servicio con el No. 63, con la cabeza del hacha inclinada hacia fuera de la parte delantera del avión.
<Polish>: Kokarda 63 Dywizjonu. Ta kokarda, jak większość przykładów, zawiera główny punkt odznaki dywizjonu, przedstawiający ramię trzymające topór bojowy, w towarzystwie uderzającej żółto-czarnej szachownicy. Kokarda była umieszczona wzdłuż nosa samolotów Hawker Hunter w służbie Dywizjonu 63, z głową topora skierowaną od przodu samolotu.
<Czech>: The roundel of No. 63 Squadron. This roundel like most examples incorporates the focal point of the squadron badge into the marking, which displays an arm grasping a battleaxe, accompanied by the striking yellow and black checkerboard. The roundel was positioned along the nose of the Hawker Hunters in service with No. 63, with the head of the axe angled away from the front of the aircraft.

The roundel was positioned along the nose of the Hawker Hunters in service with No. 63, with the head of the axe angled away from the front of the aircraft.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 63 飞\t行\t中\t队\t识\t别\t徽\t标。\t与\t其\t他\t部\t队\t的\t同\t类\t标\t识\t一\t样，\t该\t标\t识\t在\t极\t富\t视\t觉\t冲\t击\t力\t的\t黄\t黑\t棋\t盘\t格\t条\t带\t中\t央\t饰\t有\t中\t队\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t的\t标\t志\t性\t图\t案 - 挥\t举\t战\t斧\t的\t手\t臂\t形\t象。\t这\t一\t识\t别\t条\t带\t主\t要\t见\t于\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t霍\t克\t“猎\t人”\t战\t机，\t图\t案\t中\t战\t斧\t的\t锋\t刃\t指\t向\t机\t鼻\t前\t方。
<Ukrainian>: Рондель 63-ї ескадрильї. Цей рондель, як і більшість прикладів, включає в себе центральну точку значка ескадрильї в маркування, яке відображає руку, яка стискає бойову сокиру, супроводжується яскравою жовто-чорною шаховою дошкою. Рондель розташовувався вздовж носа Hawker Hunter на озброєнні 63-ї, а головка сокири була відхилена від передньої частини літака.
<Serbian>: The roundel of No. 63 Squadron. This roundel like most examples incorporates the focal point of the squadron badge into the marking, which displays an arm grasping a battleaxe, accompanied by the striking yellow and black checkerboard. The roundel was positioned along the nose of the Hawker Hunters in service with No. 63, with the head of the axe angled away from the front of the aircraft.

<Korean>: 제63비행대의 라운델입니다. 대다수의 것과 같은 이 라운델은 비행대 배지의 초점을 표시하는 데 초점을 맞추었으며, 마킹에는 노란색과 검은색 체커보드가 함께 표시되어 있습니다. 라운델은 호커 헌터스의 기수를 따라 배치되어 있으며 도끼의 머리 부분은 항공기 전면에서 약간 각도를 준 채로 배치되어 있습니다.

<TChinese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Phi đoàn số 63. Huy hiệu tròn này, giống như hầu hết các ví dụ khác, kết hợp điểm nhấn của huy hiệu phi đoàn vào dấu hiệu, thể hiện một cánh tay cầm rìu chiến, đi kèm với bảng màu vàng nổi bật và kiểm tra màu đen và vàng. Huy hiệu tròn được đặt dọc theo mũi của các máy bay Hawker Hunter đang phục vụ tại Phi đoàn số 63, với đầu rìu hướng ra xa phía trước của máy bay.

<English>: This decal commemorates the 84th anniversary of the Battle of Britain. Each flag represents the nation of the pilot in service with the RAF during the battle, collectively known as "The Few": Great Britain, Austria, Australia, Ireland, Canada, Newfoundland and Labrador, South Africa, Jamaica, Poland, Barbados, Belgium, USA, New Zealand, France, Czechia, and Southern Rhodesia.
<French>: This decal commemorates the 84th anniversary of the Battle of Britain. Each flag represents the nation of the pilot in service with the RAF during the battle, collectively known as "The Few": Great Britain, Austria, Australia, Ireland, Canada, Newfoundland and Labrador, South Africa, Jamaica, Poland, Barbados, Belgium, USA, New Zealand, France, Czechia, and Southern Rhodesia.
<Italian>: Questa decal commemora l'84° anniversario della Battaglia di Gran Bretagna. Ciascuna bandiera rappresenta la nazione del pilota in servizio con la RAF durante la battaglia, conosciuta come "The Few" (I Pochi): Gran Bretagna, Austria, Australia, Irlanda, Canada, Terranova e Labrador, Sudafrica, Jamaica, Polonia, Barbados, Belgio, USA, Nuova Zelanda, Francia, Cecoslovacchia e Rodesia del Sud.
<German>: This decal commemorates the 84th anniversary of the Battle of Britain. Each flag represents the nation of the pilot in service with the RAF during the battle, collectively known as "The Few": Great Britain, Austria, Australia, Ireland, Canada, Newfoundland and Labrador, South Africa, Jamaica, Poland, Barbados, Belgium, USA, New Zealand, France, Czechia, and Southern Rhodesia.
<Spanish>: Esta calcomanía conmemora el 84º aniversario de la Batalla de Inglaterra. Cada bandera representa la nación del piloto en servicio con la RAF durante la batalla, conocidos colectivamente como "Los Pocos": Gran Bretaña, Austria, Australia, Irlanda, Canadá, Terranova y Labrador, Sudáfrica, Jamaica, Polonia, Barbados, Bélgica, EEUU, Nueva Zelanda, Francia, Chequia y Rodesia del Sur.
<Russian>: Эта декаль чествует 84-ю годовщину Битвы за Британию. Каждый флаг соответствует стране, чьи пилоты служили в Королевских ВВС во время битвы и получили прозвище «Немногие»: Великобритания, Австрия, Австралия, Ирландия, Канада, Ньюфаундленд и Лабрадор, Южная Африка, Ямайка, Польша, Барбадос, Бельгия, США, Новая Зеландия, Франция, Чехия и Южная Родезия.
<Polish>: Te oznaczenie upamiętnia 84. rocznicę Bitwy o Anglię. Każda flaga reprezentuje narodowość pilota służącego w RAF podczas bitwy, zbiorczo nazywanych 'Nielicznymi': Wielka Brytania, Austria, Australia, Irlandia, Kanada, Nowa Fundlandia i Labrador, Południowa Afryka, Jamajka, Polska, Barbados, Belgia, USA, Nowa Zelandia, Francja, Czechy i Rodezja Południowa.
<Czech>: This decal commemorates the 84th anniversary of the Battle of Britain. Each flag represents the nation of the pilot in service with the RAF during the battle, collectively known as "The Few": Great Britain, Austria, Australia, Ireland, Canada, Newfoundland and Labrador, South Africa, Jamaica, Poland, Barbados, Belgium, USA, New Zealand, France, Czechia, and Southern Rhodesia.
